revision.text:
{{Item|research=Natural Gas Well|sellValue={{Money|0.03}}|itemImage=Icon-raw-gas.png|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}
==Information==
'''Raw Gas''' is a fluid that can be pumped from the ground by the [[Natural Gas Well]]. '''Raw Gas''' is one of the least profitable resources, and it is highly recommended to refine it into [[LNG]].

==Usage==
As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, '''Raw Gas''' can only be used in a [[Condenser]] to create [[Water-Free Gas]]. The stated fluid can then be run through a [[Gas Refinery]], yielding [[Refined Gas]]. Using [[Natural Gas Well|Natural Gas Wells]] coupled with [[Condenser|Condensers]] to produce [[Water-Free Gas]] is comparable to directly obtaining the latter from an [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]]. The former method can be significantly more compact than the latter, not requiring any of the inputs necessary for the [[Oil Fracking Tower]] to function. However, if an [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] setup is already present, diverting the [[Water-Free Gas]] byproduct can be a viable method of sustaining a [[Refined Gas]] production chain. 

==Recipes==
