{{Item|itemImage=icon-copper-wire.png|sellValue={{money|7.31}}|research=Roller|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Copper Wire''' is an item obtained by rolling a [[Copper Plate]] using either the [[Roller]] or its industrial variant ([[Industrial Roller]]) it can also be obtained from its MK2 variant ([[Roller MK2]]). As one [[Copper Ingot]] produces six [[Copper Wire|Copper Wires]], its decreased sell price is compensated for by the said amount produced. Creating at least one unit of '''Copper Wire''' will grant the {{Badge|Roller Copper}}.

==Usage==
In the early game, '''Copper Wire''' can be sold for a profit, though it is quickly outclassed by [[Iron Coil|Iron Coils]]. It can be made into [[Insulated Wire]] for the production of [[Electric Motor|Electric Motors]], though the latter is a fairly weak source of [[Money]]. The true potential of '''Copper Wire''' shines through in the [[Microchip]] production chain, as it is one of the critical inputs in the [[Logic Assembler]].

==Recipes==
