{{Item|itemImage=Icon-plastic-pellets.png|research=Plastics|sellValue={{Money|0.87|size=8}}|resValue={{RP|25x }}}}
==Information==
'''Plastic Pellets''' are a material produced by combining [[PTA]] and [[MEG]] in the [[Plastic Production Facility]].

If the production chain seems too confusing, here is a short recipe for producing it: 

*[[Crude Oil]] + [[Steam]] = [[Paraxylene]] + [[Ethylene]] ( using [[Steam Cracking Plant]] )
*[[Crude Oil]] + [[Water]] = [[Ethanol]] ( using [[Plastic Refinery]] ) ( ''Highly recommend using [[Water Pump2]])''
*[[Ethanol]] will then be turned into [[Acetic Acid]] by running it through [[Oxidation Plant]]
*Combine [[Paraxylene]] and [[Acetic Acid]] using [[Plastic Refinery]] to make [[PTA]]

Now for [[MEG]]:

*Run [[Ethylene]] made by the [[Steam Cracking Plant]] that you placed through the[[Oxidation Plant]] to turn it into [[MEG]]

Put [[PTA]] and [[MEG]] into [[Plastic Production Facility]] and now the user can simply enjoy the gratitude of extra money making opportunities. By itself, it can be used in the [[Lithium Battery Pack]]. By having the user inputting it through a [[Plastic Molding Machine]], the user can turn it into either [[Plastic Casing]] for [[Gearbox]] production or [[Plastic Bottle]] and used by the [[Bottling Plant]], for production of various fluid bottles.[[File:Plastics production line Industralist.png|thumb|Plastics production line visual guide]]Here are all the machines required for the production of the '''Plastic Pellet''' and their cost (''might change in the future who knows'') So the user does not waste time calculating the math (''or just simply not in the game to check it'').

*[[Oil Rig]] =? (you can place as many as you like when you are rich heh) Though the price per [[Oil Rig]] is {{Money|1,200}}. The [[Large Pumpjack]] can also be used, with a cost of {{Money|120,000}}
* [[Water Pump2]] =? ( same reason as [[Oil Rig]] ) Though the price per [[Water Pump2]] is {{Money|6,000}}
* 1x [[Steam Cracking Plant]] = {{Money|150,000}}.
*2x [[Plastic Refinery]] = {{Money|200,000}} Each [[Plastic Refinery]] is {{Money|100,000}}
*2x [[Oxidation Plant]] = {{Money|400,000}} Each [[Oxidation Plant]] is {{Money|200,000}}
* 1x [[Plastic Production Facility]] = {{Money|100,000}}

Total = {{Money|850,000}} + $? from Oil Rigs and Water Pumps

==Usage==

On their own, '''Plastic Pellets''' are almost entirely worthless, selling for less than {{Money|1}}. However, their value shines in both the mid game and late game, due to their unavoidable involvement in lucrative [[Money]]-making farms. Their earliest uses are in the acquisition of [[Plastic Bottle|Plastic Bottles]] and [[Gearbox|Gearboxes]], bridging the formidable gap between [[Crankshaft|Crankshafts]] and [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold]]. '''Plastic Pellets''' are also a critical component of [[Lithium Battery Pack|Lithium Battery Packs]] and [[Microchip|Microchips]], making them invaluable for late-game [[Money]] farms. Most '''Plastic Pellet'''-producing setups cost approximately {{Money|850,000}} to construct, though said chains involved in the assembly of [[Logic Plate|Logic Plates]] do not need to be anywhere as efficient as those sustaining the assembly of other products.

