{{Item|itemImage=Icon-oak-log.png|research=Modular Tree Farm|sellValue={{Money|5.8|size=8}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
{{Quote|Fresh timber! You can convert it to Planks.}}
The '''Oak Log''' is an item obtained when a [[Farm Harvester]] harvests a [[Tree]]. Two '''Oak Logs''' are produced for each [[Tree]], though the latter grows at different speeds according to the world [[Pollution]] level. In order for the '''Oak Logs''' to be transferred and used in machines, the '''Oak Logs''' need to be collected in a [[Tree Farm Output]]. The [[Tree Farm Output]] can then be connected through pipes to a [[Sawmill]], [[Industrial Sawmill]], [[Industrial Firebox]], [[Blast Furnace]], [[Blast Furnace MK2]], [[Paper Mill]], or [[Grinder]].

==Usage==
'''Oak Logs''' sell for {{Money|5.80}}, however, the real reason to use a [[Tree Farm]] is to craft [[Chair|Chairs]], which requires '''Oak Logs''' to be processed into [[Planks]] through the usage of 3 [[Sawmill|Sawmills]]. With the [[Craft Assembler]] or [[Advanced Assembler]] as they sell for {{Money|1029.50}}, though it varies, also due to [[Pollution]]. It can also be used inside of a [[Paper Mill]] or [[Grinder]] to create [[Paper]] or an [[Industrial Firebox]] to produce [[Sodium Carbonate]], a crucial material in the [[Lithium Battery Pack]] production, or [[Coke Fuel]], which is important in metallurgy.

'''Oak Logs''' provide a crucial role in [[Steel Ingot|Steel]] production; requiring [[Coke Fuel]] made from '''Oak Logs''' to create [[Steel Ingot|Steel]]. [[Coke Fuel]] also provides an intense substitute for [[Coal]], for example a [[Foundry]] requires 2,400 units of [[Coal]] to run, while using [[Coke Fuel]] only requires 240 units.

