{{Item|itemImage=Icon-meg.png|research=Plastics|sellValue={{Money|2.9|size=8}}|resValue={{RP|0.2x }}}}
==Information==
'''MEG''' or '''Monoethylene Glycol''' is a fluid only used currently in the production of [[Plastic Pellets|Plastic]]. It is made in an [[Oxidation Plant]] by oxidizing [[Ethylene]]. '''MEG''' functions as the second ingredient needed for the [[Plastic Production Facility]] to yield [[Plastic Pellets]], and is generally regarded as easier to obtain than [[PTA]]. 

==Usage==
'''MEG''' can be combined with [[PTA]] in a [[Plastic Production Facility]] to create [[Plastic Pellet|Plastic Pellets]]. This is MEG's Only use, as selling it is counter intuitive and nets less income than the materials used to make it.

