{{Item|title1=Acetic Acid|itemImage=icon-acetic-acid.png|sellValue={{Money|14.5|size=8}}|research=Plastics|resValue={{RP|7x }}}}
==Information==
'''Acetic Acid''' is an acidic liquid that is produced from [[Ethanol]] using an [[Oxidation Plant]]. It is one of the main acids in the game, alongside [[Sulfuric Acid]] and [[Hydrochloric Acid]]. Generally, if a machine uses acid as a modifier rather than an ingredient, '''Acetic Acid''' can be used instead of [[Sulfuric Acid|Sulfuric]] or [[Hydrochloric Acid]], although '''Acetic Acid''' will usually be the weakest choice compared to the other acids.

'''Acetic Acid''' is produced by using the oil from 2 [[Oil Rig|Oil Rigs]] with the [[Water]] from one [[Water Pump]] for each [[Plastic Refinery]] used to create [[Ethanol]]. The [[Ethanol]] is then inputted to an [[Oxidation Plant]] that will then produce the '''Acetic Acid'''. 1 [[Oxidation Plant]] is capable of supporting 6 [[Plastic Refinery|Plastic Refineries]] or 24 of them if fed with [[Oxygen]] from an [[Electrolysis Plant]].

It is not optimal to use a lot of '''Acetic Acid''' as the [[Plastic Refinery]] is considerably slow and requires placing large amount of it.

==Usage==
'''Acetic Acid's''' unique use case is in [[Plastic Pellet]] production. [[PTA]] is produced when four liters of '''Acetic Acid''' are combined with one liter of [[Paraxylene]] in a [[Plastic Refinery]]. Afterward, the resultant [[PTA]] can be combined with [[MEG]] to produce [[Plastic Pellet|Plastic Pellets]], which can be fed into a [[Plastic Molding Machine]] for either [[Plastic Casing]] or [[Bottle]] production. '''Acetic Acid''' is also used for [[Gold Acid Refinery]] and [[Oil Fracking Tower]] for producing late game products. 

'''Acetic Acid''' can also be used as a modifier to boost a multitude of machines. Such as the [[Large Pumpjack]] and [[Mineshaft Drill]]. It is the weakest acid among its contemporaries, however, it is sometimes preferred by players that are primarily concerned with ease of building, cost, and space or in cases where [[Sulfuric Acid|Sulfuric]] or [[Hydrochloric Acid]] production is otherwise not a worthwhile investment. 

