{{Item|research=Copper Extracting|sellValue={{Money|5.51}}|itemImage=Icon-raw-copper.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Raw Copper''' is a raw material that is extracted by the [[Copper Drill]] and its sister extractor, the [[Advanced Copper Drill]]. Though it is typically used in early-game production chains such as those featured in [[Copper Wire]] farms, it is essential for the production of [[Logic Plate|Logic Plates]] and thus [[Microchip|Microchips]].

==Usage==
'''Raw Copper''' is primarily used as an early game source of [[Money]]. It can be sold in its raw form for a meager {{Money|5.51}} per unit, but it is highly recommended to refine it into [[Copper Wire]] as they sell for {{Money|7.3}} each, and makes 6 wires per [[Copper Ingot]], for a total of {{Money|43.8}} per Ingot.

'''Raw Copper''' can be run through an [[Electric Furnace]] and [[Ingot Molder]] to produce said [[Copper Ingot|Copper Ingots]]. The produced [[Copper Ingot|Copper Ingots]] can then be put through a [[Press]] and [[Roller]], yielding [[Copper Wire]]. Though [[Copper Wire]] sells for only {{Money|7.31}}, one [[Copper Ingot]] can be converted into six units of [[Copper Wire]]. As such, the effective price is {{Money|43.86}}, when compared to the inputted [[Copper Ingot|Copper Ingots]].

'''Raw Copper''' can also be converted into [[Drill Heads]] in a [[Lathe]], though the yielded [[Copper Drill Head|Copper Drill Heads]] are exceptionally weak and thus not recommended for use in the [[Mineshaft Drill]].

More information can be found in the [[Copper Production]] article.

