{{Item|research=Water Filtering|sellValue={{Money|29|size=8}}|itemImage=Icon-machine-oil.png|resValue={{RP|4x }}}}
==Information==
'''Machine Oil''' is a versatile liquid created by filtering [[Refined Diesel]] in a [[Filtration Plant]] or separating [[Heavy Oil]] via an [[Industrial Oil Separator]]. One liter of [[Refined Diesel]] makes 0.6L of '''Machine Oil''' while one liter of [[Heavy Oil]] makes 0.5L of M'''achine Oil'''.

'''Machine Oil''' converts the glow emitted by [[Research Station2 (old)]] from a yellow to an orange tint.

==Usage==
One of the most common uses of '''Machine Oil''' is to be used in an [[Industrial Diesel Refinery]] to produce mass amounts of [[Refined Diesel]]. However, to produce '''Machine Oil''' in the first place the player need to already have produced a decent amount of [[Refined Diesel]] to filter some into '''Machine Oil'''. Thus, to produce the needed [[Diesel]], the player should first utilize the regular [[Diesel Refinery]] to produce the needed [[Refined Diesel]] and then '''Machine Oil''' before the player move on to the upgraded version. The same principle applies to the [[Advanced Diesel Refinery]], which was an exclusive Christmas item unlockable from December 2023 to January 2024. An alternative to having to go through all three refining processes for [[Diesel]] is to use a [[Coal Liquefaction Plant]] to process the outputted [[Light Oil]] and [[Heavy Oil]] into [[Diesel]] and '''Machine Oil'''.

The [[Large Diesel Engine]] requires 0.1L of '''Machine Oil''' to run, though in turn, it makes a large amount of electricity. If the player already using [[Industrial Diesel Refinery|Industrial Diesel Refineries]] to supply the large engines, the player should combine the '''Machine Oil''' supplies with the engine and meet both demands of both machines.

'''Machine Oil''' is also used in [[Research Station2]] as an alternative to [[Water]], which will provide a good boost in research production. Although considering how much effort it takes to produce '''Machine Oil''', some people may prefer to use water anyway.

Lastly, '''Machine Oil''' is usable in a  [[HV Transformer]], requiring 0.5L/s, to reduce the [[Power]] transfer loss all the way to 1%. Granted, the [[HV Transformer]] takes very extreme amounts of '''Machine Oil''' and thus it may be better to use [[Water]] instead, even if there will be more power loss.

