{{Item|research=Steel|sellValue={{Money|50|size=8}}|itemImage=Icon-silicon.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Silicon''' is a resource that is often used to make [[Semiconductor|Semiconductors]] or [[Logic Plate|Logic Plates]]. It can be sold on its own for a fair profit, though it yields a much greater sum of [[Money]] when used in the production of [[Microchip|Microchips]].

==Usage==
When disposing of excess [[Sand]], '''Silicon''' is generally regarded as the best way of doing so, due to its relatively high sale value. Though [[Glass]] sells for {{Money|30}} more than '''Silicon''', each unit of [[Sand]] can yield up to five times as much of the latter than of the former. As such, '''Silicon''' generates {{Money|62.5}} per unit of [[Sand]], whereas [[Glass]] only yields {{Money|20}}.

However, in situations where large quantities of excess [[Sand]] are generated, melting the stated down into [[Liquid Glass]] can be preferable, as the a similar-sized [[Industrial Electric Furnace]] setup can consistently dispose more units of [[Sand]] per second than a [[Blast Furnace]].

