{{Item|itemImage=icon-crushed-bauxite.png|research=Trommel|sellValue={{Money|75}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Crushed Bauxite''' is an intermediate material produced by processing [[Bauxite Residue]] in a [[Grinder]]. It serves as an essential ingredient in the production of late-game items such as [[Microchip|Microchips]] and [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold]].

[[Bauxite Residue]] can be obtained with the [[Trommel]], [[Mineshaft Drill]], and [[Industrial Drill]]. Among these, the [[Trommel]] is the easiest to use.

Seven [[Trommel|Trommels]] inputted with [[Water]] and [[Soil]] can sustain three [[Grinder|Grinders]]. Each [[Grinder]] yields three units of '''Crushed Bauxite''' for every four units of [[Bauxite Residue]] processed.

== Usage ==
'''Crushed Bauxite''' can be refined into [[Alumina]] in a [[Blast Furnace]]. The resulting [[Alumina]] can then be further processed into [[Alumina Dust]] using a [[Grinder]], and subsequently into [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium Ingots]] through the [[Industrial Electric Furnace]] and [[Ingot Molder]].

As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, '''Crushed Bauxite''' has no other uses, only serving as a transitional material between [[Bauxite Residue]] and [[Alumina]], which is one of the main ingredients in [[Aluminium Ingot]] production, which is used in crafting [[Tire Rim|Tire Rims]], [[Semiconductor|Semiconductors]], [[Ferroaluminium Alloy Ingot|Ferroaluminium Alloy]], and [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold]].

