[[Category:Items]]{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|title1=Soil|itemImage=Icon-soil.png|research=Quarry|sellValue={{Money|2}}|resValue={{RP|0.1x }}}}
==Information==
[[Soil]] is one of the several Industrialist natural, raw resources, and it is the starting point of any player's '''Gold Production''' lines. It can be produced by putting [[Water]] into a [[Soil Excavator]]. It is extremely rich in resources but needs to be further processed into usable [[Rich Soil]] to be turned into [[Gold]]. The latter can be turned into the profitable, mid-late game [[Gold Ingot]] for huge profits if assembled correctly.

==Usage==
The main use of '''Soil''' is to produce [[Gold]] through [[Rich Soil]] in a [[Trommel]]. The other outputs of the [[Trommel]] are [[Sand]], [[Gravel]], and [[Bauxite Residue]]. [[Gravel]] can be [[Grinder|ground]] back into [[Sand]] and reused in the [[Glass]] industry or applied to the [[BlastFurnace|Blast Furnace]] with [[Coal]] or [[Coke Fuel]] and then to the [[LogicAssembler|Logic Assembler]] line (as precursor to the [[Semiconductor]]). [[Gravel]] can also be used as an ingredient when producing a [[Filter]] in the [[Advanced Assembler]], doubling the output as opposed to using [[Sand]] to make one.

==Recipes==
{{Production|time=20|Mamyflux=50kMF|output1=soil|Output1Amount=60|machine=Quarry|output2=clay|Output2Amount=60}}
{{Production|input1=water|Input1Amount=240|time=20|Mamyflux=50kMF|output1=soil|Output1Amount=120|machine=Quarry|output2=clay|Output2Amount=120}}
{{Production|input1=soil|Input1Amount=12|time=12|Mamyflux=33kMF|output1=gravel|Output1Amount=12|machine=Grinder}}
{{Production|input1=water|Input1Amount=80|input2=soil|Input2Amount=40|time=28|Mamyflux=17.9kMF|output1=rich-soil|Output1Amount=16|output2=bauxite-residue|Output2Amount=8|output3=gravel|Output3Amount=4|output4=sand|Output4Amount=4|machine=Trommel}}
{{Production|input1=soil|Input1Amount=120|time=16|Mamyflux=1.25MMF|output1=gravel|Output1Amount=120|machine=Grinder MK2}}

==Trivia==
* '''Soil''' is not dirt, but dirt is '''inside''' '''Soil'''. The intricate balance between microbes, [[Gravel]], plant [[Residue]] and [[Water]] is broken once the player extract the minerals from '''Soil''', leaving behind only what one would find in dirt. Dirt is unusable in the agriculture industry, but '''Soil''' is, as the latter is more fertile, wet and has organic matter, and the former is hard, dry and infertile.
*One can find '''Soil''' in places with dense forestry or thriving plant life.

