{{Item|title1=Rich Soil|itemImage=Icon-rich-soil.png|research=Gold Refining|sellValue={{Money|4|}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Rich Soil''' is created by inputting [[Soil]], extracted by a [[Soil Excavator]] into a [[Trommel]], Grinding [[Treated Rock]], or putting [[Medium Earth Fragment|Medium Earth Fragments]] into a [[Gold Acid Refinery]]. It can be used for making 8k, 10k, and 18k [[Gold]].

==Usage==
'''Rich Soil''' can be put into a [[Pressurized Water Filter]] or [[Gold Acid Refinery]] to be made into various qualities of [[Gold]]. 

When '''Rich Soil''' is inputted into a [[Pressurized Water Filter]] and made into [[8 Karat Gold]] that cannot be upgraded further in any machinery (Not recommended).

'''Recommended Option 1'''

# When [[Rich Soil]] is inputted into a [[Gold Acid Refinery]] with [[Acetic Acid]], it is refined into [[10 Karat Gold]]. 
# Followed by a [[Pressurized Water Filter]], it will be refined into [[12 Karat Gold]].
# Followed by another [[Gold Acid Refinery]], it will be refined into [[18 Karat Gold]].
# Finally, another [[Pressurized Water Filter]], it will be refined into [[24 Karat Gold]].

'''Recommended Option 2''' 

# When [[Rich Soil]] is inputted into a [[Gold Acid Refinery]] with [[Sulfuric Acid]], it is then refined into [[18 Karat Gold]].
# Followed by a [[Pressurized Water Filter]] it will be refined into [[24 Karat Gold]].
For more information check out the [[Gold]].

