{{Item|research=Industrial Roller|sellValue={{Money|8,500}}|itemImage=Icon-ferroaluminium-magnet.png|resValue={{RP|120x }}}} ==Information== '''Ferroaluminium Magnets''' are a valuable product created by rolling two [[Ferroaluminium Alloy|Ferroaluminium Alloys]], a combination of [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium]] and [[Iron Ingot|Iron]] in [[Alloyer]], into an [[Industrial Roller]]. The '''Ferroaluminium Magnets''' sell at a base price of {{Money|8,500}}.
==Usage== The '''Ferroaluminium Magnet''' can be used in place of some of the [[Electromagnet]] required when making [[Electric Motor]]. This is only recommended if the player has spare [[Bauxite Residue]], as [[Electric Motor]] manufacturing is complex and not worth the small profit margin.
'''Ferroaluminium Magnet''' sell for a relatively high price; however, [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold]] has a higher profit compared to the required effort when producing [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminum]]. Generally, the profits earned from selling [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold]] outweigh the added complexity, but '''Magnets''' are overall less complicated. Should the player focus solely on '''Magnets''', whatever happens to the excess [[Rich Soil]] is up to the player; refining past 8-Karat [[Gold]] yields more money, at the expense of an additional setup.
==Recipes== {{Production|input1=ferroaluminium-alloy-ingot|Input1Amount=2|time=6|Mamyflux=1125MF|output1=ferroaluminium-magnet|Output1Amount=1|machine=Industrial Roller}} {{Production|input1=electromagnet|Input1Amount=4|input2=ferroaluminium-magnet|Input2Amount=0.2|input3=steel-rod|Input3Amount=2|input4=steel-plate|Input4Amount=4|input5=machine-oil|Input5Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=electric-motor|Output1Amount=1|machine=Advanced Assembler}}
==Trivia== *[[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium]] is used in some real magnetic alloys; however, these do not usually include [[Iron Ingot|Iron]]. Instead, they contain elements like cobalt or manganese, while [[Iron Ingot|Iron]] is often alloyed with cobalt, nickel, or neodymium. *Even though the Items Navbox states that it is a finalized item, it is not because of the existence of the [[Electric Motor]]. **In fact, the [[Electric Motor]] has the same problem, just that it might not count as it is an ingredient to a limited, the [[Cat]]. **This has since been rectified.
[[Category:Items]] {{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|research=Industrial Electric Furnace|sellValue={{Money|800}}|itemImage=icon-aluminium-ingot.png|resValue={{RP|65x }}}}

== Information ==
'''Aluminium Ingots''' are used in the production of [[Purple Gold Ingot]]s, [[Ferroaluminium Magnet]]s, and [[Semiconductor]]s, which are required for [[Microchip]] manufacturing. The recommended use of '''Aluminium Ingots''' is in [[Semiconductor]] production. 

The creation of '''Aluminium Ingots''' involves multiple processing steps. [[Bauxite Residue]] is first processed in a [[Grinder]], then combined with [[Coke Fuel]] in a [[Blast Furnace]]. The resulting material is ground again in a [[Grinder]] and subsequently melted in an [[Industrial Electric Furnace]]. The molten output is then molded into '''Aluminium Ingots''' using an [[Ingot Molder]].

It is advised that players verify the appropriate input ratios before placing machinery. Additionally, users should ensure sufficient funds are available to sustain the full production process before initiating construction, as the total setup cost exceeds several million dollars.

