[[Category:Items]]
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-alumina.png|research=Blast Furnace|sellValue={{Money|100}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Alumina''' is a material that can be synthesized by blasting [[Crushed Bauxite]] in a [[Blast Furnace]], though [[Coke Fuel]] must be used for said process. This is very important as it is the foundation of the [[Aluminium Ingot]], which when inserted into an [[Alloyer]] along with [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]] or [[Gold Ingot|Gold Ingots]] makes [[Ferroaluminium Alloy Ingot|Ferroaluminium Alloy Ingots]] and [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold Ingots]] respectively. The former can be rolled into [[Ferroaluminium Magnet|Ferroaluminium Magnets]], whereas the latter can be sold for a large amount of [[Money]]. In a [[Purple Gold Ingot]] production line, it is highly recommended to have an [[Pipes|Overflow Gate Pipe]] for [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium Ingots]], unless a perfect ratio is achieved.  

==Usage==
'''Alumina''' can be converted to [[Alumina Dust]] in a [[Grinder]], which can then be [[Industrial Electric Furnace|melted]] and [[Ingot Molder|molded]] into [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium Ingots]]. As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, it has no other uses, only serving as a bridge between [[Crushed Bauxite]] and [[Alumina Dust]]. Unlike almost all other [[Blast Furnace]] recipes, '''Alumina''' requires the use of [[Coke Fuel]], which can add an extra layer of complexity to its production line. Though a [[Tree Farm]] can be used to supply the [[Blast Furnace]] with [[Coke Fuel]], the [[Advanced Oil Separator]] is preferred due to its consistency and lesser toll on the world's model count. 

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=coke-fuel|Input1Amount=4|input2=crushed-bauxite|Input2Amount=4|time=5|Mamyflux=15kMF|output1=alumina|Output1Amount=6|machine=Blast Furnace}}
{{Production|input1=alumina|Input1Amount=4|time=12|Mamyflux=33kMF|output1=alumina-dust|Output1Amount=4|machine=Grinder}}
{{Production|input1=alumina|Input1Amount=40|time=16|Mamyflux=1.25MMF|output1=alumina-dust|Output1Amount=40|machine=Grinder MK2}}

==Trivia==
*'''Alumina''' is another word for [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium]] Oxide, and the terms can be used interchangeably.
*'''Alumina''' has the only icon where there is only a chemical formula, and not a visual molecular model.
