==Trivia==
*In real life, '''Alumina Dust''' is turned into [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium]] via electrolysis instead of just melting it.
*'''Alumina Dust''' has a strange and unpleasant smell.

[[Category:Items]]
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-liquid-aluminium.png|research=Industrial electric furnace|sellValue={{Money|200}}|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}
==Information==
'''Liquid Aluminium''' is the liquid variant of the [[Aluminium Ingot]], and it can be solidified in an [[Ingot Molder]]. It is an unavoidable bridge item in the [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium]] production line, closing the gap between [[Alumina Dust]] and [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium Ingots]].

==Usage==
In almost all cases, '''Liquid Aluminium''' should be solidified into [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium Ingots]], as the latter sells for two times as much [[Money]] as the former. Additionally, this comes at a scarce cost, as the [[Ingot Molder]] required to perform this step requires little [[Power]] and [[Money]] to operate.

