{{Item|research=Alloyer|sellValue={{Money|1,100}}|itemImage=Icon-molten-ferroaluminium-alloy.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Molten Ferroaluminium Alloy''' is a valuable fluid formed by an [[Alloyer]] from combining [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium Ingots]] and [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]]. It can be cast into [[Ferroaluminium Alloy Ingot|Ferroaluminium Alloy Ingot]] in an [[Ingot Molder]].

Ideally, '''Molten Ferroaluminium Alloy''' should be processed into [[Ferroaluminium Magnet|Ferroaluminium Magnets]] and sold, as this provides a high profit margin.

==Usage==
As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, the sole purpose of '''Molten Ferroaluminium Alloy''' is to be molded into [[Ferroaluminium Alloy Ingot|Ferroaluminium Alloy Ingots]]. Though setting up an entire [[Bauxite Residue]] refining chain for the sole purpose of producing [[Ferroaluminium Magnet|Ferroaluminium Magnets]] is unviable, diverting excess [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium Ingots]] created in a [[Gold]] production chain for use in [[Ferroaluminium Magnet|Ferroaluminium Magnets]] production can be a profitable method of disposal.

