{{Item|research=Steel|sellValue={{Money|10}}|itemImage=Icon-iron-mix.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Iron Mix''' is a powder made from [[Coal]] or [[Coke Fuel]] and [[Iron Powder]] in a [[Blast Furnace]],[[Blast Furnace MK2]], or [[Industrial Kiln]]. It is used to make [[Iron Ingot]] and [[Steel Ingot|Steel]] as effectively possible. Smelting and molding it into [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]] and then making it into [[Steel Ingot|Steel]] is more efficient than turning it directly into [[Steel Ingot|Steel]].

==Usage==
'''Iron Mix''' is effectively a more efficient, and a effective way to create [[Liquid Iron]], as it produces more [[Liquid Iron]] per unit than [[Raw Iron]] and is mainly used in large scale [[Steel Ingot|Steel]] production. Although it is efficient, [[Treated Raw Iron]] holds the title for most efficient, as it produces 5 [[Liquid Iron]] per unit, compared to the ~2 [[Liquid Iron]] per unit gathered from using [[Iron Mix]].

