{{Item|research=Iron|sellValue={{Money|5.8}}|itemImage=Icon-raw-iron.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
[[Raw Iron]] is an invaluable ore directly involved in the production of [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]]. It can be obtained via the [[Iron Drill]], [[Mineshaft Drill]], or [[Industrial Drill]].

==Usage==
'''Raw Iron''' can be smelted into [[Liquid Iron]] to be turned into [[Iron Ingot]]<nowiki/>s with the [[Ingot Molder]] in various ways such as:

* With the [[Advanced Electric Furnace|(Advanced)]] [[Electric Furnace]].
* Being crushed into [[Iron Powder]] with a [[Grinder]] to produce [[Iron Mix]] in a [[Blast Furnace]] and then smelted, for a more efficient way.
* And for late game players, producing [[Treated Raw Iron]] in a [[Chemical Reactor]] and smelted with an [[Industrial Electric Furnace]], being the most efficient method to produce lots of [[Liquid Iron]].

As '''Raw Iron''' is one of the most useful items in the game, some of it's most relevant uses are:

* Producing [[Iron Coil|Iron Coils]] for the best early game [[Money Making]] method.
* Being the core of [[Steel Drill Head]] used in the [[Mineshaft Drill]], a key machine during late game.
* Producing [[Iron Plate^2|Iron PlateÂ²]] for a good mid game [[Money Making]] method.
* Making [[Graphite-Iron Electrode|Graphite-Iron Electrodes]] for [[Lithium Battery Pack|Lithium Battery Packs]] in order to research the [[Precision Assembler]].
* Being necessary in any [[Steel Ingot]] related item.
* Making [[Iron Drill Head|Iron Drill Heads]] for the [[Mineshaft Drill]]. (Highly advised to use [[Steel Drill Head]] instead.)
* Making [[Nails]] to produce [[Chair|Chairs]] for an early game [[Money Making]] method. (Recommended to produce [[Iron Coil|Iron Coils]] instead.)

