== Trivia ==

* The [[Press MK2]]'s recipe for the '''Iron Plate<sup>2</sup>'''  is not shown in the [[Recipe Book]], therefore making it a secret recipe.

{{Items Navbox}}

{{Hatnote}}
{{Item|research=Coal extracting|sellValue={{Money|5.22|size=8}}|itemImage=icon-coal.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Coal''' is a raw ore normally obtained by a [[Coal Drill]], [[Advanced Coal Drill]], or [[Mineshaft Drill]] but can also be obtained through the [[Trommel]], [[Gold Acid Refinery]], or [[Pressurized Water Filter]]. It is most typically used for [[Power]] generation for the early game (through the [[Coal Generator|Coal]] [[Compact Coal Power Plant|Generators]] and [[Firebox]]) and late game (through the [[Coal Power Plant|Huge Coal Power Plant]]). '''Coal''' can also be used in several factory setups to smelt higher grade ingredients.

Being a crude item, production and consumption of '''Coal''' can be seen as cheap, but heavily polluting. This can be partly canceled out by using [[Advanced Coal Drill|Advanced Coal Drills]] or the [[Mineshaft Drill]] instead, but they of course have the drawback of requiring greater amounts of [[Power]] to maintain. 

==Usage==
'''Coal''' has an extremely wide variety of uses throughout the entire game, from power generation to being an ingredient for a number of highly complicated setups in factories.

*'''Coal''' can be sold in a [[Truck Depot]] depot for cash, and it is done so at the very start in the game. However, this very quickly becomes obsolete due to its low value per unit and should not be used as a consistent source of income.
*'''Coal''' is the main ingredient for the various [[Coal|Coal Machines]], as well as the only fuel used by the [[Firebox]], a machine that burns said '''Coal''' to heat up [[Water]]. Both of these machines can be used to create [[Power]], the former using the '''Coal''' directly and the latter using it to produce [[Steam]].
*'''Coal''' is used in a [[Blast Furnace]] to smelt and produce [[Steel]] or [[Iron Mix|Iron]]/[[Copper Mix|Copper Mixes]]. It can also be combined with [[Oak Log|Oak Logs]] to make [[Coke Fuel]], an enhanced fuel item used to increase the efficiency of [[Blast Furnace|Blast Furnaces]], [[Foundry|Foundries]], and [[Industrial Firebox|Industrial Fireboxes]]. Note that '''Coal''' cannot replace [[Coke Fuel]] when attempting to make [[Alumina]].
*'''Coal''' can be shredded in a [[Grinder]], yielding [[Black Dye]]. The stated product can then be used for the production of [[Toy|Toys]] and [[Powdered Tungsten Carbide]].
*'''Coal''' is used in late game power generation via the [[Coal Power Plant]], a machine that yields hot [[Distilled Water]] for use in the [[Heat Exchanger]] and [[Modular Turbine]].
* '''Coal''' can be used in the [[Foundry]] for the mass production of ingots. However, it is greatly outclassed by [[Coke Fuel]] for this purpose.

