==Trivia==
*'''Coal''' is the first resource introduced in the game, as well as the first product that can be sold. It is also part of the tutorial.
*In-game '''Coal''' is bituminous, as it can be converted into [[Heavy Oil]] and [[Light Oil]] in the [[Coal Liquefaction Plant]].

[[Category:Raw Materials]]
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|title1=Steam|sellValue={{money|0.03|size=8}}|itemImage=Icon-steam.png|research=Boiler|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}
==Information ==
'''Steam''' is a fluid created by heating [[Water]] in a heat source ([[Geothermal Well]], [[Firebox]] or [[Gas Burner]]) and then boiling it with a [[Boiler]]. '''Steam''' has a multitude of uses, comparable to [[Water]]. It can also be used to produce other items using machines like a [[Steam Cracking Plant]] or a [[Industrial Oil Separator]] to make [[Diesel]] or [[Machine Oil]]. '''Steam''' has kickstarted the Industrial Revolution as a thermal and kinetic energy medium and also has a huge variety of uses in real life.   

==Usage==
One of the many uses of '''Steam''', but most common, is to make [[Power]] via a turbine ([[Steam Turbine]], not recommended, or [[Large Turbine]]). Turbines do not directly consume '''Steam''' but rather cool it back down into [[Water]], generating an average of {{Power|200-400kMF/s}} (per [[Large Turbine]]) in the process. It is '''heavily''' recommended to use [[Large Turbine]] in place of the smaller [[Steam Turbine]], as the '''Steam''' usage is substantially larger, and the power generation is higher.    

[[Water]] converts into '''Steam''' and back at a set rate of 3L of [[Water]] -> 90L of '''Steam''' ({{Ratio|2|1|30}} ratio). Most machines comply with this rate. (Notable outliers include the [[Steam Cracking Plant]] and the [[Geothermal Well]]).    

'''Steam''' can be created by using a [[Boiler]] or a [[Coal Generator]]. The latter is not advised to produce '''Steam''', as it only makes a few liters of '''Steam'''.     
*'''Steam''' is one of the cheapest gases you can sell, going for {{Money|0.03}}/L.
*The {{Ratio|2|1|30}} volume conversion rate of [[Water]] to '''Steam''' is possible in real life (considering pure H<sub>2</sub>O) at 50 bar/725.18 psi. Saturated water at {{Heat|263.94}} has a volume of 1.286L/kg and '''Steam''' (saturated vapor at {{Heat|263.94}}) has a volume of 39.448L/kg. This is a {{Ratio|2|1|30.6}} ratio.
*'''Steam''' will lose around {{Heat|0.01}} for every connection that it travels through. [[Gold Fluid Storage Silo|Silos]] can counteract this by a special method called heat confining (use silos instead of pipes). It is unknown how or why the silos conserve heat, but it is a specific case usage for Silos, other than [[Residue]] storage.
*One [[HMVT]] can withstand the power generation of up to 20 [[Large Turbine|Large Turbines]] (average of five per [[Power]] node at ~{{Power|300kMF/s}}).
*'''Steam''' can also make power in the limited [[Small Turbine]] which is more '''Steam''' efficient but requires five to match the '''Steam''' consumption of one [[Large Turbine]].

