{{Item|research=Steel|sellValue={{Money|92.8}}|itemImage=Icon-steel-rod.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Steel Rods''' are considered an early to mid-game item, used in everything from bridges to buildings for added strength! While they only bring in a modest [[Resource Sell Price|Profit]] when sold, their real value shines once they are crafted into more advanced items such as [[Crankshaft|Crankshafts]] or [[Gearbox|Gearboxes]].

==Production==

===Recommended===
'''Steel Rods''' can be produced in either a [[Roller]] or [[Industrial Roller]] by inputting two [[Steel Ingot|Steel Ingots]]. The latter rolls the materials at a much faster pace at the cost of consuming extra [[Power]].

===Not Recommended===
[[Steel Ingot|Steel Ingots]] can also be run through a [[Roller MK2]], processing them into [[Steel Coil|Steel Coils]] instead of the desired '''Steel Rods'''. However, the aforementioned [[Steel Coil|Steel Coils]] can be processed in a [[Lathe]], turning them into '''Steel Rods'''. The proper ratio of [[Roller MK2|Roller MK2s]] to [[Lathe|Lathes]] is two to one.

==Usage==
As previously mentioned, '''Steel Rods''' can be sold directly or used in further processing. To craft a [[Crankshaft]], combine two '''Steel Rods''' with four [[Gear|Gears]] in either a [[Craft Assembler]] or an [[Advanced Assembler]]. Alternatively, to create a [[Gearbox]], use two [[Plastic Casing|Plastic Casings]] and two '''Steel Rods''' with four [[Gear|Gears]] in an [[Advanced Assembler]].

