{{Item|itemImage=Icon-hot-crude-oil.png|research=Oil Boiling & Separating|sellValue={{Money|0.14|size=8}}|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}

== Information ==
'''Hot Crude Oil''' is a fluid obtained by heating [[Crude Oil]] in a [[Liquid Boiler]], raising its temperature to approximately {{Heat|600}}. Once heated, the fluid remains suitable for processing in a [[Crude Oil Separator]] even after cooling.

== Usage ==
'''Hot Crude Oil''' is processed in a [[Crude Oil Separator]] to produce more refined fuels, including [[Crude Diesel]] and [[Gasoline]]. This expands the utility of [[Crude Oil]] for various industrial applications.

== Recipes ==
{{Production|input1=crude-oil|Input1Amount=0.75|time=1|Mamyflux=10kMF|output1=hot-crude-oil|Output1Amount=0.75|machine=Liquid Boiler}}  
{{Production|input1=hot-crude-oil|Input1Amount=1.5|time=1|Mamyflux=2.2kMF|output1=crude-diesel|Output1Amount=0.675|output2=gasoline|Output2Amount=0.3|output3=residue|Output3Amount=0.3|machine=Crude Oil Separator}}

== Trivia ==
* '''Hot Crude Oil''' contains more thermal energy than other liquids when used in a [[Boiler]], allowing it to function as a coolant in the [[Boiler]]'s cooling loop. However, this method is complex and presents challenges in disposal. The [[Power]] required to produce [[Hot Crude Oil]] exceeds the energy gains from its use, making the process inefficient. [[Water]] is a more effective and practical alternative for cooling purposes.
* '''Hot Crude Oil''' is treated as a distinct item from standard [[Crude Oil]] within the game systems, despite the similarity in names.

