{{Item|itemImage=Icon-residue.png|sellValue={{Money|-5.8}}|research=Oil Separating|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}
==Information==
'''Residue''' is an polluting waste byproduct produced by separating many of the fluids and items in the game in their byproducts through the machinery. It is a waste fluid product that cannot be used in further production and is sold for a negative price (unless [[Residue Bottle|bottled]]). Unlike any other liquid, it will severely pollute the environment if dumped via a [[Liquid Dump]] or [[Liquid Burner]].

==Usage ==
Since '''Residue''' serves no purpose and sells for a negative amount of [[Money]], disposing of it can sometimes be a challenge, especially in the early game. If current production lines cannot sustain the steep cost of selling [[Residue]], or if the [[Residue]]-producing machine is temporary, it can occasionally be beneficial to store it in a [[Gold Fluid Storage Silo]].

In the [[Game Difficulties|Normal]] difficulty, silos filled with '''Residue''' will not pollute the world if they are deleted. This can be an easy way to get rid of '''Residue''' without having to pay for anything, being useful in early game situations. However, harder difficulties will drastically increase the world's [[Pollution]] level upon the deletion of any silo, greatly decreasing their viability. However, silos can still be used in the early game, though it is recommended to drain them later with a [[Liquid Truck Depot]] or [[Large Liquid Truck Depot]].

Ideally, '''Residue''' can be loaded into [[Liquid Truck Depot|Liquid Truck Depots]] and sold, but with a loss of [[Money]]. Using this method is beneficial due to the lack of required maintenance, as simply storing '''Residue''' can cause production lines to clog up and shut down if the [[Gold Fluid Storage Silo|Gold Fluid Storage Silos]] are completely filled. Do note that multiple [[Gas Refinery|Gas Refineries]] or [[Scrubber|Scrubbers]] will require more than one [[Liquid Truck Depot]] due to the colossal amount of '''Residue''' that they produce.

'''Residue''' should never be removed in any [[Liquid Dump]] or [[Liquid Burner]] unless the outputted residue amount is very little, like in the [[Diesel Refinery]]. No matter how tempting it is, the amount of emitted [[Pollution]] and thus increased [[Scrubber]] requirement will by far outweigh the slight monetary toll of selling it.

It is possible to put '''Residue''' inside plastic [[Bottle|Bottles]], which will provide no [[Money]] loss nor gain when sold. This method is discouraged, as it is less profitable than selling the components separately. This is because selling the '''Residue''' and [[Bottle|Bottles]] will provide {{Money|30}} of profit versus the {{Money|0}} that it grants when bottled, although this does remove the '''Residue'''. 

