==Trivia== 
*'''Residue''' can be bottled using a [[Bottling Plant]] but the resulting product sells for {{Money|0}}.
*'''Residue''' can be run through a [[Filtration Plant]], however attempting to filter it will simply result in producing more '''Residue''' by adding 0.4 extra '''Residue''' more than the input of the '''Residue''' through the [[Filtration Plant]].
*'''Residue''' can be input into the [[Scrubber]] in order to produce more [[Residue]] and increase the world's [[Pollution]].
* The [[April Fools 2024|April Fools 2024 Update]] added the [[Residue Refinery]] to turn '''Residue''' into [[Crude Oil]], [[Heavy Oil]], and [[Crude Diesel]] as a joke where [[Residue Refinery]] outputs were item outputs.
*As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, burning 200 liters of '''Residue''' per second in a [[Liquid Burner]] is the best way to release [[Pollution]], emitting {{Pollution|1,728}}/hr.
*The composition of '''Residue''' is unknown, but definitely contains some hydrocarbon products like Ethane and Propane as they cannot be extracted from [[Water-Free_Gas|Water Free Gas]] and probably come out in the '''Residue''' output in the [[Gas Refinery]]. It also probably contains some [[Heavy Oil]] and Bitumen due to it being output from the [[Crude Oil Separator]].
*As of {{Update|1.0}}, the [[Gas Refinery]] produces the most residue out of all machines, with a 3L/s production rate. 
**Selling this amount of residue would make {{Money|-17.4}}/s.
**[[Liquid Dump|Dumping]]/[[Liquid Burner|Burning]] this amount of residue would make {{Pollution|15.92}} [[Pollution]] an hour.
**Storing this amount in [[Gold Fluid Storage Silo|Gold Fluid Storage Silos]] would fill one every 92 hours (rounded) or 3.85 days.

