[[Category:Items with a negative sell price]]

{{Item|research=Iron|sellValue={{Money|43.85}}|itemImage=Icon-iron-coil.png|resValue={{RP|4x }}}}{{PageHeader|Items}} ==Information== The '''Iron Coil''' is an [[Items|Item]] created by processing an [[Iron Ingot]] through both a [[Press]] and a [[Roller]].
The '''Iron Coil''' is primarily sold for [[Money]]. It was historically one of three major early-game competitors for [[Money|Income]] generation, alongside the [[Chair]] and the [[Iron Plate^2]] before the meta solidified. The [[Chair]] is limited by the number of [[Sawmill|Sawmills]] required and slow production speed, resulting in a significantly lower income compared to an equivalent '''Iron Coil''' setup. The [[Iron Plate^2]] was less efficient because each [[Iron Plate]] could be used to produce either 0.25 [[Iron Plate^2|Iron Plates^2]] or 2 '''Iron Coils'''. Despite its higher sell price, this translated to {{Money|73.95}} earned per [[Iron Plate]] for the [[Iron Plate^2]] versus {{Money|87.7}} for the '''Iron Coil'''.
Beyond its role as a sellable [[Items|Item]], the '''Iron Coil''' is also a component in the [[Filter]], an essential item for operating the [[Exhaust Stack]] and, by extension, the [[Coal Power Plant]]. Filters allow the removal of [[Exhaust]] gases that would otherwise exceed the handling capacity of even large-scale [[Scrubber]] setups.
While the '''Iron Coil''' is an efficient early-game [[Items|Item]] to sell, its role is eventually surpassed. More profitable production chains, such as those meant to produce [[LNG]], may become the primary source of [[Money|Income]] once sufficient [[Money|Funds]] and infrastructure are available. Transitioning to such setups often requires reconfiguration of [[MamyFlux|Power]] systems, such as adopting a [[Modular Diesel Engine]] in place of a [[Firebox]]-fueled [[Boiler]]/[[Large Turbine]] arrangement.
==Production== The standard production chain for the '''Iron Coil''' begins with [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]], which are converted into [[Iron Plate|Iron Plates]] via a [[Press]] or [[Sawmill]], and then into '''Iron Coils''' using a [[Roller]]. While the final steps are consistent, the production of [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]] defines two main methods of '''Iron Coil''' farming. [[File:Basic Iron Coil Farm.png|alt=Flowchart of 15:5:1:10:8|thumb|15:5:1:10:8]] The first method relies on [[Iron Drill|Iron Drills]] to supply [[Raw Iron]], which is smelted into [[Liquid Iron]] in an [[Electric Furnace]] and molded into [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]] with an [[Ingot Molder]]. This approach has a low upfront cost but produces relatively high [[Pollution]] per unit of [[Money|income]] and scales poorly. It is often used when only small amounts of '''Iron Coils''' are required, such as in [[Filter]] production or beginner setups.
A typical setupâone of which is belowâusing this method produces {{Money|175.4}}/s and costs {{Money|17,638}}. The Flowchart for this setup is to the right. {| class="wikitable" ![[Iron Drill|Iron Drills]] ![[Electric Furnace]] ![[Ingot Molder]] ![[Sawmill|Sawmills]] ![[Roller|Rollers]] |- |15 |5 |1 |10 |8 |}
The second method uses [[Blast Furnace|Blast Furnaces]] to create [[Iron Mix]], reducing the number of [[Iron Drill|Iron Drills]] required. [[Iron Powder]] is first produced in a [[Grinder]] from [[Raw Iron]], while [[Coke Fuel]] is created from [[Oak Log|Oak Logs]] and [[Coal]] in a [[Blast Furnace]]. These are then combined in another [[Blast Furnace]] to produce [[Iron Mix]], which is smelted into [[Liquid Iron]] and molded into [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]]. The process then follows the same steps as the first method.
A sample setupâshown belowâusing this method produces {{Money|438.5}}/s while requiring significantly fewer [[Iron Drill|Iron Drills]] (11 instead of 38 for equivalent output). {| class="wikitable" ![[Tree|Trees]] ![[Coal Drill|Coal Drills]] ![[Blast Furnace]] ![[Iron Drill|Iron Drills]] ![[Grinder|Grinders]] ![[Blast Furnace]] ![[Electric Furnace]] ![[Ingot Molder]] ![[Sawmill|Sawmills]] ![[Roller|Rollers]] |- |6<ref>Depends on [[Pollution]]. Excess [[Tree|Trees]] are often used, such as 10.</ref> |1 |1 |11 |3 |1 |2 |3 |25 |20 |}
==Recipes== {{Production|input1=iron-plate|Input1Amount=2|time=8|Mamyflux=750MF|output1=iron-coil|Output1Amount=4|machine=Roller}} {{Production|input1=iron-plate|Input1Amount=2|time=6|Mamyflux=1125MF|output1=iron-coil|Output1Amount=4|machine=Industrial Roller}} {{Production|input1=iron-plate|Input1Amount=20|time=8|Mamyflux=50kMF|output1=iron-coil|Output1Amount=40|machine=Roller MK2}} {{Production|input1=coal|Input1Amount=5|input2=iron-coil|Input2Amount=2|input3=paper|Input3Amount=2|input4=sand|Input4Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=filter|Output1Amount=1|machine=Advanced Assembler}} {{Production|input1=coal|Input1Amount=5|input2=iron-coil|Input2Amount=2|input3=paper|Input3Amount=2|input4=gravel|Input4Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=filter|Output1Amount=2|machine=Advanced Assembler}} {{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-iron-plate.png|research=Press|sellValue={{Money|70.18}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Iron Plate''' is an item made out of [[Iron]] made by putting [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]] from an [[Ingot Molder]] into a [[Press]] or [[Sawmill]]. 

==Usage==
The '''Iron Plate''' can be turned into [[Iron Plate^2|Iron Plate<sup>2</sup>]] in a [[Press]], [[Industrial Press]], or [[Press MK2]]. Both the [[Press]] and [[Press MK2]] produce '''Iron Plates''' from [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]] in a {{Ratio|2|1|1}} ratio, whereas the [[Sawmill]] and its industrial sister yield four '''Iron Plates''' for every [[Iron Ingot]] inputted. As such, utilizing the [[Sawmill]] or [[Industrial Sawmill]] can be greatly beneficial in setups where yield is more important than simplicity or size, truly shining in the mass production of [[Iron Coil|Iron Coils]] during the early game. 

