{{Production|machine=Advanced Electric Furnace|input1=iron-mix|Input1Amount=6.4|time=5|Mamyflux=24kMF|output1=liquid-iron|Output1Amount=14}}

== Trivia ==

* Processing [[Treated Raw Iron]] in an [[Industrial Electric Furnace]] yields the most '''Liquid Iron''' per unit and it is recommended to use this when creating [[Iron Ingot|Iron]] to be used in making [[Drill Heads]] for the [[Mineshaft Drill]].
* '''Liquid Iron''' can also be used as [[Boiler]] coolant and still be used, to get some energy back. Doing so will get L'''iquid Iron''' into negative temperatures, which is physically impossible.
