{{Item|itemImage=Icon-refined-gas.png|sellValue={{Money|0.29}}|research=Gas refinery|resValue={{RP|0.01x }}}}
==Information==
'''Refined Gas''' is made by running [[Water-Free Gas]] through a [[Gas Refinery]] with 1/3 of the input turned into [[Residue]] (constituting the not-pure part of the water-free gas). In other words, when 90 liters of [[Water-Free Gas]] are inputted, 60 liters of '''Refined Gas''' are yielded, with the byproduct of [[Residue]].

'''Refined Gas''' sells for {{Money|0.29}} per liter, and as such its raw sale is highly discouraged. Its low sale value is amplified by the [[Gas Refinery|Gas Refinery's]] large [[Residue]] output, causing the net profit of one [[Gas Refinery]] to be as low as {{Money|0.6}} per second.

== Usage ==
'''Refined Gas''' can be combusted in a [[Gas Burner]] to make {{Heat|400}} [[Water]] or utilized in an [[LNG Plant]] to produce [[LNG]], a liquid that sells for {{Money|160}} per liter.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=water-free-gas|Input1Amount=90|time=1|Mamyflux=60kMF|output1=refined-gas|Output1Amount=60|machine=Gas Refinery|output2=residue|Output2Amount=3}} 
{{Production|machine=Gas Burner|time=1|Mamyflux=0MF|output1=water|Output1Amount=30|input1=refined-gas|Input1Amount=30|input2=water|Input2Amount=30}} 
{{Production|machine=LNG Plant|time=1|Mamyflux=2.25MMF|output1=lng|Output1Amount=6.6|input1=refined-gas|Input1Amount=120}}
{{Production|time=6|Mamyflux=2MMF|input1=refined-gas|Input1Amount=120|input2=oxygen|Input2Amount=60|output1=ethanol|Output1Amount=60|output2=hydrogen|Output2Amount=30|machine=Advanced Oxidation Plant}}
{{Production|time=1|Mamyflux=500kMF|input1=steam|Input1Amount=90|input2=refined-gas|Input2Amount=60|output1=hydrogen|Output1Amount=15|machine=Chemical Plant}}

==Trivia==
*Canonically, '''Refined Gas''' is pure [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methane Methane]. This claim is best supported by its item icon, depicting the CH<sub href="Category:Fluids">4</sub> molecule.
