{{Top-bottle}}{{Item|sellValue={{Money|72.5}}|itemImage=Icon-plastic-bottle.png|research=Plastics|resValue={{RP|30x }}}}
==Information==
'''Plastic Bottles''' are made by processing [[Plastic Pellets]] in a [[Plastic Molding Machine]], assuming the latter is set to produce '''Plastic Bottles''' instead of [[Plastic Casing]]. The resulting '''Plastic Bottles''' can then be filled with a multitude of different liquids including [[Water]], [[Filtered Water]], [[Crude Oil]], [[Refined Diesel]], and [[Residue]]. 

==Usage==
'''Plastic Bottles''' are a critical input of the [[Bottling Plant]], which greatly increases the monetary value of liquids processed into their bottled variant. For every liquid except [[Residue]], the bottled selling price is higher than the combined values of the '''Plastic Bottle''' and liquid used to make the aforementioned.

Bottling [[Residue]] is not recommended as a [[Residue Bottle]] sells for {{Money|0}} and selling it also produces [[Pollution]] and even though it gets rid of the [[Residue]], it also makes less profit than selling the 8 [[Residue]] and the '''Plastic Bottle''' used in the recipe individually.

