{{Top-bottle}}{{Item|title1=Oil Bottle|itemImage=Icon-oil-bottle.png|research=Water Bottling|sellValue={{Money|208.8|size=8}}|resValue={{RP|20x }}}}
==Information== An '''Oil Bottle''' is a [[Plastic Pellets|Plastic]]-based sellable product created by combining [[Crude Oil]] and [[Bottle|Plastic Bottles]] inside the [[Bottling Plant]]. Each bottle sells for {{Money|208.8}}, making it one of the more profitable bottled items.
Despite its selling price being greater than most bottled items, '''Oil Bottles''' are inefficient to produce due to the high value of [[Crude Oil]] production. Players generally find that other bottled products like the [[Water Bottle]] are more efficient, since [[Filtered Water]] is cheap and easy to mass-produce.
==Usage== Currently, '''Oil Bottles''' have no practical purpose besides being sold for [[Money]]. However, given the cost of using [[Crude Oil]] as input, selling them is rarely worth the effort. As such, their only practical use is selling them for their comedic value.
If a player is looking to bottle something for profit, [[Water Bottle|Water Bottles]] is generally a much better choice due to [[Filtered Water]] being extremely easy to mass produce.
==Recipes== {{Production |input1=crude-oil |Input1Amount=8 |input2=plastic-bottle |Input2Amount=1 |time=3.5 |Mamyflux=2.86kMF |output1=oil-bottle |Output1Amount=1 |machine=Bottling Plant }}
==Trivia== * The '''Oil Bottle''' has the second highest sell price per unit among all bottled items.
