{{Top-bottle}}{{Item|title1=|itemImage=Icon-cheap-water-bottle.png|research=Water Bottling|sellValue={{Money|130.50}}|resValue={{RP|5x }}}} ==Information== '''Cheap Water Bottles''' are created by processing [[Water]] and [[Plastic Bottle|Plastic Bottles]] in a [[Bottling Plant]]. Once the [[Filtration Plant]] is unlocked, they are superseded by [[Water Bottle|Water Bottles]], as the said item sells for 29% more [[Money]].
Despite the complexity of producing [[Plastic Pellets|Plastic]] for the [[Plastic Bottle|Plastic Bottles]], a '''Cheap Water Bottle''' sells for only {{Money|130.50}}. Using the same amount of [[Plastic Pellets|Plastic]], a [[Gearbox]] will sell for much more [[Money]] than '''Cheap Water Bottles'''.
== Recipes == {{Production|input1=water|input2=plastic-bottle|time=3.5|Mamyflux=2.86kMF|output1=cheap-water-bottle|machine=Bottling Plant|Input1Amount=8|Input2Amount=1|Output1Amount=1}}
==Trivia== *Assuming that both the [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] and [[Electrolysis Plant]] operate with no material loss, each '''Cheap Water Bottle''' contains approximately 50 grams of [[Table Salt|Salt]] dissolved within it. **For reference, filling the exact same [[Plastic Bottle]] with seawater would cause it to contain roughly 280 grams of [[Table Salt]]. **Given the same assumptions, each '''Cheap Water Bottle''' has around 6.6 grams of [[Lithium Ore|Lithium]] dissolved in it. *If the item icon for [[Dirty Lithium Sulfate]] perfectly represents the substance's composition, one '''Cheap Water Bottle''' contains roughly 0.95 grams of [[Chlorine]], 0.75 grams of nitrogen, and 0.83 grams of phosphorus. {{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|title1=Plank<sup>2</sup>|itemImage=Icon-plank^2.png|research=Press|sellValue={{Money|40.6|size=8}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
The '''Plank<sup>2</sup>''' is produced by putting a [[Planks]] into a [[Press]], at a {{Ratio|2|1|0.25}} ratio.

Although the '''Plank<sup>2</sup>''' sells for more than a singular normal [[Planks|Plank]], it is important to note that the value of '''Plank<sup>2</sup>''' is lower than the four [[Planks]] used to produce it. Compared to four normal [[Planks]] with a combined value of {{Money|52.4}}, the '''Plank<sup>2</sup>''' only has a value of {{Money|40.6}}; processing one [[Planks|Plank]] through a [[Press]] reduces the value of the plank by {{Money|2.95}}. Therefore, it is more profitable to simply sell the [[Planks]] or instead use them to produce [[Chair|Chairs]].

==Usage==
Akin to the [[Iron Plate^2|Iron Plate<sup>2</sup>]], the '''Plank<sup>2</sup>''' currently has no purpose other than being sold. It has one incredibly niche use, as producing [[Planks]] and '''Plank<sup>2</sup>s''' do not produce any [[Pollution]], save for selling them in a [[Truck Depot]]. Given the stated information, converting [[Planks]] into '''Plank<sup>2</sup>s''' produces approximately one third of the emitted [[Pollution]] upon their sale, due to the more compact nature of a '''Plank<sup>2</sup>'''.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=planks|Input1Amount=1|time=4|Mamyflux=6250MF|output1=plank^2|Output1Amount=0.25|machine=Press}}
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|sellValue={{Money|65.54}}|itemImage=Icon-iron-ingot.png|research=Iron|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Iron Ingot''' is one of the most useful and important items in the game, it's obtaining by casting [[Liquid Iron]] in an [[Ingot Molder]]. The ways to obtain [[Liquid Iron]] are by melting [[Raw Iron]] in a [[Electric Furnace]] for slow but affordable way, by smelting [[Iron Mix]] in a [[Electric Furnace]] for bigger [[Liquid Iron]] needs or smelting [[Treated Raw Iron]] in an [[Industrial Electric Furnace]] for the best way to produce [[Liquid Iron]].   

== Usage ==
'''Iron ingot''' has a variety of uses, some of them are:

Â· Producing [[Iron Coil]] for the best early game [[Money Making]] method.

Â· Being the core of [[Steel Drill Head]] used in the [[Mineshaft Drill]] which is a core machine in the late game.

Â· Producing [[Iron Plate^2]] for a good mid game [[Money Making]] method.

Â· Making [[Graphite-Iron Electrode]] needed for [[Lithium Battery Pack]] needed for researching the [[Precision Assembler]].

Â· Being necessary in any [[Steel Ingot]] related item.

Â· Making [[Iron Drill Head]] for the [[Mineshaft Drill]]. (Highly advised to use [[Steel Drill Head]] instead).

Â· Making [[Steel Ingot|Steel]] for [[Nails]] to produce [[Chair|Chairs]] for an early game [[Money Making]] method. (Though it is advised to use iron to produce [[Iron Coil|Iron Coils]] instead).

