{{Rewrite}}{{Limited}}
{{Item|sellValue={{Money|8,000|size=8}}|itemImage=Icon-uranium.png|research=Iron}}
For other uses, see [[Uranium (disambiguation)]].
==Information==
'''Uranium''', not to be confused with [[Raw Uranium]], is a resource that can be obtained using the [[Uranium Drill]], a variant of the [[Iron Drill]] available during the [[Christmas Event 2023]]. This resource has a high sell value, but it is not necessarily profitable because of the [[Uranium Drill|Uranium Drill's]] major drawbacks, most notably its extraordinary [[Power]] consumption and drilling time. As such, one [[Uranium Drill]] can only yield {{Money|4}} per second, making it worse than a [[Large Pumpjack]] in terms of raw sale value.

==Usage==
'''Uranium''' can only be sold as of version {{Update|1.0}} and has no current use in factories.

==Recipes==
{{Production|time=180|Mamyflux=1.2GMF|output1=Uranium|Output1Amount=0.1|machine=Uranium Drill}}

== Trivia ==

* Despite being '''Uranium,''' it cannot be used in the recipes that [[Raw Uranium]] can use such as [[Mixed Uranium Oxides|Mixed Uranium Oxide.]]
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-coke-fuel.png|research=Steel|sellValue={{Money|18|size=8}}|resValue={{RP|9x }}}}
==Information==
'''Coke Fuel''' is produced by inputting both [[Coal]] and [[Oak Log|Oak Logs]] into a [[Blast Furnace]] or [[Blast Furnace MK2]] and can be produced in mass using [[Heavy Oil]] in an [[Advanced Oil Separator]]. It is necessary for the production of [[Aluminium Ingot|Aluminium Ingots]], and can additionally be used as an alternative to [[Coal]] when making [[Steel Ingot|Steel]], and [[Copper Mix|Copper]]/[[Iron Mix|Iron]] Mixes. '''Coke Fuel''' can be run back into the [[Blast Furnace MK2]] to make '''Coke Fuel''' while using fewer [[Oak Log|Oak Logs]] (100x '''Coke Fuel''' from 10x [[Oak Log|Logs]] instead of 300x '''Coke Fuel''' from 50x [[Oak Log|Logs]]). 

