{{Item|itemImage=Icon-light-oil.png|caption-itemImage=Sometimes oil is heavy, so here you go!|tier=3|research=Oil Fracking<br>Advanced Diesel Refining|sellValue={{Money|7}}|resValue={{RP|0.1x}}}}

== Information ==
Light Oil is a fluid produced through multiple manufacturing methods and serves as a key component in the oil processing industry. The most efficient method of production is the [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]], which yields 10 liters per second. Alternative production methods include the [[Industrial Oil Separator]], [[Advanced Oil Separator]], [[Steam Cracking Plant]], and [[Coal Liquefaction Plant]].

== Uses ==
Light Oil can be refined into [[Diesel]] using an [[Industrial Oil Separator]] by combining it with [[Steam]]. It may also be processed in a [[Steam Cracking Plant]] to produce [[Crude Diesel]]. Light Oil is commonly used in the generation of [[Machine Oil]] for industrial applications.

