{{Item|itemImage=Icon-hydrogen-sulfide.png|research=Industrial Diesel Refining|sellValue={{Money|8}}|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}
==Information==
'''Hydrogen Sulfide''' is a noxious fluid that can only be produced in the [[Advanced Oil Separator]]. It provides the only way to get [[Liquid Sulfur]] without using the [[Mineshaft Drill]], and is a keystone of almost any [[Sulfuric Acid]] production line. The latter is invaluable in [[Gold]] production or as an acid in the [[Mineshaft Drill]].

==Usage==
As previously stated, '''Hydrogen Sulfide''' provides the most straightforward way to obtain [[Sulfuric Acid]], as it does not require the use of the [[Mineshaft Drill]]. Running [[Crude Oil]] through the [[Advanced Oil Separator]] is generally regarded as the best way to produce '''Hydrogen Sulfide''', as it yields the highest quantity of said gas. The [[Light Oil]] produced as a byproduct can either be routed to another [[Advanced Oil Separator]], or simply converted to [[Crude Diesel]] in a [[Steam Cracking Plant]] and burned for [[Power]].

