==Information==
'''Sulfur Dioxide''' is a crucial step in the production of [[Sulfuric Acid]], bridging the gap between [[Liquid Sulfur]] and [[Sulfur Trioxide]]. Though it sells for significantly less [[Money]] than the [[Liquid Sulfur]] which it is produced, its redeeming quality comes in the form of the versatile [[Sulfuric Acid]] of whose production chain it is a part.

