{{Item|itemImage=Icon-sulfur-trioxide.png|research=Plastics|sellValue={{Money|2.5}}|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}
==Information==
'''Sulfur Trioxide''' is a gas that is very similar to its precursor compound [[Sulfur Dioxide]], due to both chemicals functioning as a bridge between [[Liquid Sulfur]] and [[Sulfuric Acid]]. Though selling for {{Money|0.5}} more than its direct antecedent, it is still exponentially less profitable than the sale of raw [[Sulfur]], leaving its only practical use in the production of [[Sulfuric Acid]].

If a large amount of [[Sulfuric Acid]] is needed and an excess of '''Sulfur Trioxide''' is present, some [[Sulfuric Acid]] can be recirculated back into the acid-producing [[Chemical Reactor]]. This will cut the recipe time in half at the expense of doubling [[Power]] consumption, making it viable primarily in large-scale [[Sulfuric Acid]] setups. The [[Chemical Reactor|Chemical Reactor's]] [[Water]] input can be replaced with [[Distilled Water]] in order to compensate for the consumed [[Sulfuric Acid]], though this requires the use of an [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] or [[Water Treatment Plant]].

