{{Item|sellValue={{Money|57}}|itemImage=icon-gasolinee10.png|research=Oil fracking|resValue={{RP|13x }}}} ==Information== '''GasolineE10''' is created by inputting [[Gasoline]] and [[Ethanol]] into a [[Chemical Reactor]], producing ten liters of '''GasolineE10''' each cycle. It can either be sold for a profit in the [[Large Liquid Truck Depot]] or [[Large Liquid Truck Depot]] or used to produce [[Power]] in a [[Gasoline Generator]].
Each liter of '''GasolineE10''' can yield up to{{Power|2.4MMF}} over ten seconds.
==Usage== '''GasolineE10''' can actually be used as a somewhat decent source of [[Power]], thanks to how little input the [[Gasoline Generator]] consumes. However, any [[Power]] plant utilizing '''GasolineE10''' as a fuel source will take an absurd toll on the model count, thanks to how many [[Gasoline Generator|Gasoline Generators]] are required to fully burn the output of one [[Chemical Reactor]]. Just one [[Chemical Reactor]] producing '''Gasoline E10''' can sustain up to one thousand [[Gasoline Generator|Gasoline Generators]] at once.
Alternatively, '''GasolineE10''' can be sold for a notable profit. While this approach does not generate any [[Power]], it places a significantly lesser burden on the global model count.
==Recipes== {{Production|input1=gasolinee10|Input1Amount=0.1|time=10|Mamyflux=-24kMF|machine=Gasoline Generator}} {{Production|input1=gasoline|Input1Amount=9|input2=ethanol|Input2Amount=1|time=6|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=gasolinee10|Output1Amount=10|machine=Chemical Reactor}}
==Trivia== *The "E10" in '''GasolineE10''' references the ratio of [[Gasoline]] to [[Ethanol]]. As such, '''GasolineE10''' contains 90% of the former and 10% of the latter. [[Category:Oil based items]] [[Category:Fluids]]{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|sellValue={{money|1}}|itemImage=icon-fracking-oil.png|research=Oil Fracking|resValue={{RP|0.2x }}}}
==Information==
[[Fracking Oil]] is a special type of oil made from the [[Oil Fracking Tower]] at a rate of 12.5L/s. Its main use is being put into the [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] to make 40 [[Heavy Oil]], 80 [[Light Oil]], 10 [[Naphtha]], 20 [[Gasoline]], 720 [[Water-Free Gas]], and 20 [[Crude Oil]] with 10 [[Residue]] coming out as a byproduct.

==Usage==
[[Naphtha]] can be made by separating [[Fracking Oil]] in an [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] and said output can then be used to produce [[Rubber]] in a [[Chemical Reactor]]. [[Fracking Oil]], when paired with [[Steam]], can also be used in an [[Advanced Oil Separator]] to produce a large quantity of [[Heavy Oil]], though it outputs [[Residue]] as a byproduct. This [[Heavy Oil]] can be used to synthesize [[Coke Fuel]] in the [[Advanced Oil Separator]], but it is drastically outclassed by [[Heavy Oil]] produced in the [[Coal Liquefaction Plant]].

Additionally, '''Fracking Oil''' can be inserted into an [[Industrial Oil Separator]], yielding [[Crude Oil]]. This is best used for the bulk acquisition of the stated, viable for fueling large arrays of [[Coal Liquefaction Plant|Coal Liquefaction Plants]].

