{{Item|itemImage=Icon-lithium-battery-pack.png|research=Advanced Assembler|sellValue={{Money|85,000}}|resValue={{RP|180x }}}}
==Information==
{{Quote|Even more valuable power?}}
The '''Lithium Battery Pack''' is the final stage in [[Lithium]] production, which cannot be processed further and can be sold for {{money|85,000}}. Ten '''Lithium Battery Packs''' must be sold in order to unlock the [[Logic Assembler]]. Even though <b>Lithium Battery Packs</b> sell more than [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold Ingots]], it is recommended that the player only sell them to unlock the [[Logic Assembler]].

==Usage==
'''Lithium Battery Packs''' can be made in [[Advanced Assembler]] with [[Charged Lithium-Ion Battery|Charged Lithium-Ion Batteries]], [[Rubber]], [[Copper Plate|Copper Plates]]. It is the second-most complex item to make, significantly easier than [[Microchip|8x64 Microchips]].

As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, '''Lithium Battery Packs''' can only be sold. Due to the complexity and relative inconsistency of their production chain, creating a permanent '''Lithium Battery Pack''' factory is discouraged. Though they sell for a large sum of [[Money]], they are still greatly outclassed by [[Microchip|Microchips]]. However, assuming 2 [[Advanced Assembler|Advanced Assemblers]] running at maximum capacity, enough [[Charged Lithium-Ion Battery|Charged Lithium-Ion Batteries]] would be made to make {{Money|2125/s}}, a decent enough income.

Ratios for '''Lithium Battery Pack''' production can be found on the [[Machine Ratios]] page.

With its high RP value and cost, it is also recommended to have an option to be fed into a [[Research Station3]] or [[Research Station4|4]] instead of simply being sold, as each lithium battery pack would generate {{RP|1800}} at minimum assuming the research points are still under the RP cap and both inputs have different items.

