== Information ==
{{Item|title1=Lithium Sulfate|sellValue={{Money|100}}|itemImage=Icon-lithium-sulfate.png|caption-itemImage=let him cook.|tier=3|research=Lithium|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
'''Lithium Sulfate''' is an item in ''Industrialist'' used to make [[Lithium Carbonate]], leading to the production of [[Lithium Battery Pack|Lithium Battery Packs]]. Due to its relatively low sale value of {{Money|100}}, it should not be sold on its own, instead ideally used to produce [[Uncharged Lithium-Ion Battery|Uncharged Lithium-Ion Batteries]], and later on, [[Lithium Battery Pack|Lithium Battery Packs]]. The former sells for {{Money|2,000}}, and the latter is valued at {{Money|85,000}}, making the extra processing steps worth the effort.

==Usage==
'''Lithium Sulfate''' can be synthesized with two unique recipes, though it is only used to form [[Lithium Carbonate]]. For larger-scale setups, processing [[Lithium Ore]] directly into '''Lithium Sulfate''' is recommended, due to the easy scalability, though cleaning [[Dirty Lithium Sulfate]] in a [[Pressurized Water Filter]] is encouraged for temporary setups.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=dirty-lithium-sulfate|Input1Amount=10|input2=water|Input2Amount=20|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=residue|Output1Amount=10|output2=lithium-sulfate|Output2Amount=10|machine=Pressurized Water Filter}}
{{Production|input1=sulfuric-acid|Input1Amount=1.4|input2=lithium-ore|Input2Amount=4|input3=sodium-carbonate|Input3Amount=2|time=2|Mamyflux=1.5MMF|output1=lithium-sulfate|Output1Amount=4|machine=Chemical Reactor}} 
{{Production|input1=water|Input1Amount=10|input2=lithium-sulfate|Input2Amount=8|input3=sodium-carbonate|Input3Amount=4|time=4|Mamyflux=750kMF|output1=lithium-carbonate|Output1Amount=4|machine=Chemical Reactor}}
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-sodium-carbonate.png|sellValue={{Money|8}}|research=Industrial firebox|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Sodium Carbonate''' is an item that is essential in making [[Uncharged Lithium-Ion Battery|Uncharged Lithium-Ion batteries]] and later, [[Lithium Battery Pack|Lithium Battery Packs]]. To obtain '''Sodium Carbonate''', [[Oak Log|Oak Logs]] must be burnt in an [[Industrial Firebox]], with just one of the latter yielding sixteen of the former. Though the [[Industrial Firebox]] must be cooled with [[Water]] when burning said [[Oak Log|Oak Logs]], the heated coolant can simply be recirculated back into the [[Industrial Firebox]], not even requiring any external cooling.

