{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|research=Logic Assembler|sellValue={{Money|0}}|itemImage=Icon-microchip-scrap.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Microchip Scraps''' are an unwanted material created by the [[LogicAssembler|Logic Assembler]] when an incorrect [[Logic]] signal is sent into it.

'''Microchip Scraps''' can be recycled into [[Gold Ingot|Gold Ingots]] with either a [[Chemical Reactor]] or a [[Grinder]], but [[Sulfuric Acid]] must be used in both recipes.

==Usage==
Akin to [[Residue]] and [[Exhaust]], '''Microchip Scraps''' serve no in-game purpose, and are generally undesirable. However, unlike the aforementioned waste fluids, '''Microchip Scraps''' cause no loss in [[Money]] upon being sold, making them a much less punishing waste product. Recycling them into [[Gold Ingot|Gold Ingots]] is generally not worth the spent [[Sulfuric Acid]], causing their sale to be the most effective method of disposal.

==Recipes==
{{Production|output1=microchip-scrap|Output1Amount=|machine=Logic Assembler}}{{Production|input1=microchip-scrap|Input1Amount=5|input2=sulfuric-acid|Input2Amount=5|machine=Chemical Reactor|time=6|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=gold-ingot|Output1Amount=1}}
{{Production|input1=microchip-scrap|Input1Amount=5|input2=sulfuric-acid|Input2Amount=0.5|machine=Grinder|time=12|Mamyflux=33kMF|output1=gold-ingot|Output1Amount=0.5}}
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|sellValue={{Money|60}}|itemImage=icon-dirty-lithium-sulfate.png|research=Chemical Reactor|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Dirty Lithium Sulfate''' is a step of an alternative way of producing [[Lithium Sulfate]], preferred when a [[Lithium Ore Drill]] is unnecessary. '''Dirty Lithium Sulfate''' can be created by combining [[Lithium Brine]] and [[Sulfuric Acid]] in a [[Chemical Reactor]] and can be purified into [[Lithium Sulfate]] with a [[Pressurized Water Filter]]. 

== Usage ==
Dirty Lithium Sulfate is best used in temporary [[Lithium Battery Pack]] setups, as it is easier to set up at the cost of being significantly less efficient and scalable than the alternative, it is not recommended for long term [[Lithium Sulfate|Lithium]] Production, as it is inefficient.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=lithium-brine|Input1Amount=6|input2=sulfuric-acid|Input2Amount=0.9|time=2|Mamyflux=1.5MMF|output1=dirty-lithium-sulfate|Output1Amount=4|machine=Chemical Reactor}}
{{Production|input1=dirty-lithium-sulfate|Input1Amount=10|input2=water|Input2Amount=20|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=residue|Output1Amount=10|output2=lithium-sulfate|Output2Amount=10|machine=Pressurized Water Filter}}

==Trivia==
*If the item icon is to be followed, '''Dirty Lithium Sulfate''' is polluted with [[Chlorine]], nitrogen, phosphorus, and various other compounds.
