{{Item|research=Electrolysis|sellValue={{Money|80|size=8}}|itemImage=Icon-hydrochloric-acid.png|resValue={{RP|10x }}}}
==Information==
'''Hydrochloric Acid''', as of {{Update|1.0}}, has a total of seventeen appearances, twelve being a usage and five being an output. These are listed below, in the Recipes section, and is <u>CRITICAL</u> in turning [[Condensate]] back into [[Distilled Water]], more information provided in the [[Polisher]] page, such as ratios. Its better to use the [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] method ( which involves water into [[Concentrated Salt Solution]] + [[Distilled Water]]. Separate [[Concentrated Salt Solution]] into [[Chlorine]] via [[Electrolysis Plant]]. Then combine [[Hydrogen]] [from separating [[Water]] into [[Oxygen]] and [[Hydrogen]] in [[Electrolysis Plant]]], [[Chlorine]] and [[Distilled Water]] to get '''Hydrochloric Acid'''), and not try and get [[Sulfuric Acid]] and [[Table Salt]].

There is a debate on which is better [[Sulfuric Acid]] or '''Hydrochloric acid'''. Thought making LARGE amounts of [[Sulfuric Acid]] requires smaller setups and uses less models this only applies when needing a lot of acid. In small or medium setups '''Hydrochloric Acid''' is way better because it's less complex and takes less time to build than a [[Treated Rock]] [[Sulfuric Acid]] setup.

==Usage==
'''Hydrochloric Acid,''' mentioned above, has a fair share of uses, along with its fair share of fun facts. This acid is used for the following conditions;

*Boost machines such as the [[Large Pumpjack]] and the [[Mineshaft Drill]], being stronger than [[Acetic Acid]] but weaker than [[Sulfuric Acid]], except in the [[Mineshaft Drill]] when drilling to 6km down deep.

*Treat [[Raw Copper]] and [[Raw Iron]] will result in their ingot yields being multiplied by 10.

*Used in a [[Gold Acid Refinery]] to refine [[Earth Fragments|Medium or Deep Earth Fragments]] to produce [[Lithium Brine]] and [[Rich Soil]], or a small amount of [[Coal]]. The latter is logically not worth doing at all, as there are objectively better ways to produce [[Coal]]. (Or do it, after all this is a wiki, not a strict instruction manual.)

*Mixed with [[Earth Fragments|Deep Earth Fragments]] in a [[Trommel]] to obtain [[Gold|18-Karat Gold]] and [[Bauxite Residue]], both of which are vital for the production of [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold]].

