==Trivia==
*'''Hydrochloric Acid''' is the third type of acid to be added in the game, added in the {{Update|0.11}} Heavy Industry update.
*It is the best option for any machine that uses acids.
*It is crafted with [[Hydrogen]] and [[Chlorine]], both of which are obtainable via the [[Electrolysis Plant]].
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|sellValue={{Money|15}}|research=Grinder|itemImage=Icon-treated-rock.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
The '''Treated Rock''' is an item created by placing [[Deep Earth Fragment|Deep Earth Fragments]] into a [[Grinder]]. It is not recommended to directly sell the '''Treated Rock''', as the [[Deep Earth Fragment|Deep Earth Fragments]] used to produce it sell for over six times its price.

==Usage==
'''Treated Rocks''' are typically valued for their [[Sulfur]] content, as refining them into [[Sulfur]] via the [[Chemical Reactor]] can at times be preferable to using the [[Advanced Oil Separator]] in conjunction with an [[Oxidation Plant]], especially for large scale production.

Additionally, '''Treated Rocks''' can be processed into [[Gold]] in either the [[Gold Acid Refinery]] or [[Trommel]], functioning as an alternative to procuring [[Rich Soil]]. Running '''Treated Rocks''' through the [[Gold Acid Refinery]] is heavily discouraged, as the yielded [[8 Karat Gold]] cannot be refined further. Processing '''Treated Rocks''' in the [[Trommel]] can serve as a viable method of extracting [[Gold]] in bulk quantities, useful for large-scale [[Microchip]] or [[Purple Gold Ingot|Purple Gold]] factories. However, if [[Hydrochloric Acid]] is available, it is generally considered better to simply place the [[Deep Earth Fragment|Deep Earth Fragments]] used to produce the '''Treated Rocks''' into a [[Trommel]] instead, as this stated method will yield [[18 Karat Gold]] in large quantities.

In a vast majority of cases, '''Treated Rocks''' should never be run though a [[Pressurized Water Filter]]. Doing so will degrade them into [[Rock|Rocks]], an extremely common and unprofitable output of the [[Mineshaft Drill]].

