{{Item|sellValue={{Money|5}}|itemImage=Icon-liquid-lead.png|research=Mineshaft Drill|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}
==Information==
[[Liquid Lead]] is a fluid that is currently, can only be used to make [[Lead Ingot|Lead Ingots]]. As with all other liquid metals, it sells for much less than its solid form, the [[Lead Ingot]]. The aforementioned solid is not of much use either, as it can only be processed into [[Leaded Gasoline]], a fuel that is both unprofitable and inefficient. 

== Usage ==
'''Liquid Lead''' has no general purpose, as its useless in the money making aspect, and to make [[Leaded Gasoline]], which is inefficient, it is mostly used when [[Raw Lead|Raw lead]] is a byproduct and the player wants extra [[Money|Cash]]

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=raw-lead|Input1Amount=5|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=liquid-lead|Output1Amount=5|machine=Industrial Electric Furnace}} 
{{Production|input1=liquid-lead|Input1Amount=8|time=4|Mamyflux=150MF|output1=lead-ingot|Output1Amount=4|machine=Ingot Molder}}

== Trivia ==
The [[Liquid Lead]] texture is the only texture of a liquid metal that is not alike other liquid metal textures, as other liquid textures are a molten, orange water drop texture with a small icon of the liquid's ingot form, while the [[Liquid Lead]] texture is only a gray droplet.{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|title1=Lead Ingot|sellValue={{Money|25}}|itemImage=Icon-lead-ingot.png|caption-itemImage=Toxic Brick|tier=4|research=Mineshaft Drill|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
[[Lead Ingot]] is an intermediate item added in update {{Update|0.11.0}} that is currently only used to create [[Tetraethyllead]] in the [[Chemical Reactor]]. '''Lead Ingots''' are produced from [[Raw Lead]] extracted by the [[Mineshaft Drill]], which yields large amounts of [[Raw Lead]] at deeper depths. A single [[Mineshaft Drill]] at a two-kilometer depth yields approximately ten units of [[Raw Lead]] per second, making the usage of a [[Foundry]] highly recommended. 

While the [[Foundry]] is the most efficient method of production, it has high [[Power]] and [[Money]] demands. Players who are unable to meet these requirements can use ten [[Industrial Electric Furnace|Industrial Electric Furnaces]] and three [[Ingot Molder|Ingot Molders]] as a substitute, though this alternative requires more space and increases overall [[Model count]].

==Usage==
As of the Nuclear Update, '''Lead Ingots''' are used to produce [[Tetraethyllead]] in the [[Chemical Reactor]] and to store items in the [[Underground Waste Facility]], [[Tetraethyllead]] is used to create [[Leaded Gasoline]], which can be used in the [[Satellite Dish Controller]] and the [[Gasoline Generator]] However, [[Leaded Gasoline]] is less efficient than [[Diesel]] in producing power, with fewer ways to use [[Leaded Gasoline]] in producing power.

Due to its low selling price of only {{Money|25}} and the poor efficiency of producing '''Lead Ingots''', producing lead should '''ONLY''' be used in the [[Underground Waste Facility]] or for the 30x RP point bonus from the [[Satellite Dish Controller]].

==Recipes==
