{{Item|sellValue={{Money|21}}|itemImage=Icon-tetraethyllead.png|research=Mineshaft Drill|resValue={{RP|7x }}}}
==Information==
'''Tetraethyllead''' is a solid item produced by mixing [[Ethanol]] and [[Lead Ingot|Lead Ingots]] in a [[Chemical Reactor]]. Though it is valued at {{Money|16.18}} more than the ingredients used in its synthesis, it is still inviable for yielding a significant profit.

==Usage==
As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, '''Tetraethyllead''' can only be used to synthesize [[Leaded Gasoline]], a potent fuel for the [[Gasoline Generator]]. When the {{Ratio|2|1|10}} ratio of '''Tetraethyllead''' to [[Leaded Gasoline]] is taken into account, each unit of the former can yield up to{{Power|50MMF}} when converted into the latter. However, the practicality of this [[Power]] generation method is greatly hindered by the [[Gasoline Generator|Gasoline Generator's]] nuances, most notably its overconsumption of fuel and small processing capability.

On its own, '''Tetraethyllead''' should not be sold, as the profit margin is exceptionally small, especially when the bulk quantity of [[Drill Heads]] and [[Power]] required to produce it is taken into account.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=gasoline|Input1Amount=9|input2=tetraethyllead|Input2Amount=1|time=6|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=leaded-gasoline|Output1Amount=10|machine=Chemical Reactor}}
{{Production|input1=ethanol|Input1Amount=4|input2=lead-ingot|Input2Amount=1|Mamyflux=600kMF|time=5|output1=tetraethyllead|Output1Amount=10|machine=Chemical Reactor}}
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|sellValue={{Money|112}}|itemImage=Icon-leaded-gasoline.png|research=Mineshaft Drill|resValue={{RP|23x }}}}
==Information==
'''Leaded Gasoline''' is a fluid that, apart from selling, currently is only used in a [[Gasoline Generator]]. It sells for {{Money|73.36}} more than its required ingredients, causing it to be a moderately profitable item to sell. It also functions as the most potent fuel for the [[Gasoline Generator]], with each liter producing{{Power|1MMF}} over 10 seconds. It is also quite good to use in the [[Satellite Dish Controller]] due to its RP bonus.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=leaded-gasoline|Input1Amount=0.1|machine=Gasoline Generator|Mamyflux=-100kMF|time=5}}
{{Production|input1=gasoline|Input1Amount=9|input2=tetraethyllead|Input2Amount=1|time=6|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=leaded-gasoline|Output1Amount=10|machine=Chemical Reactor}}

==Trivia==
*In real life, selling and burning '''Leaded Gasoline''' is illegal worldwide. This is due to the contained [[Lead Ingot|Lead]] entering the atmosphere and causing [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lead_poisoning Lead Poisoning].
*The drop of [[Gasoline]] in '''Leaded Gasoline'''<nowiki/>'s icon has the [[Tetraethyllead]] icon scattered inside.
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|research=Advanced Assembler|sellValue={{Money|20}}|itemImage=icon-filter.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Filters''' are produced in the [[Advanced Assembler]], composed of [[Coal]], [[Iron Coil|Iron Coils]], [[Paper]], and either [[Sand]] or [[Gravel]]. [[Sand]] is much easier to produce than [[Gravel]], only requiring one [[Sand Excavator]] as opposed to the more [[Power]]-intensive [[Soil Excavator]] and [[Grinder]] duo, but using [[Gravel]] yields double the '''Filters.''' However, using [[Sand]] is recommended as it takes up less space and uses less [[Power]] and [[Gravel]] should only be used when there is a lack of [[Paper]]/[[Oak Log|Oak Logs]] to reduce their requirement in a '''Filter''' production line.

The lack of [[Paper]]/[[Oak Log|Oak Logs]] can further reduced by providing [[Chlorine]] to the [[Paper Mill]] to double the [[Paper]] output.

==Usage==
'''Filters''' can be sold for {{Money|20}} per unit or used by an [[Exhaust Stack]] to reduce the [[Pollution]] caused from releasing [[Exhaust]] into the atmosphere, the latter being the main reason why '''Filters''' are produced.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=coal|Input1Amount=5|input2=iron-coil|Input2Amount=2|input3=paper|Input3Amount=2|input4=sand|Input4Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=filter|Output1Amount=1|machine=Advanced Assembler}}
{{Production|input1=coal|Input1Amount=5|input2=iron-coil|Input2Amount=2|input3=paper|Input3Amount=2|input4=gravel|Input4Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=filter|Output1Amount=2|machine=Advanced Assembler}}

==Trivia==
*'''Filters''' reduce the [[Exhaust Stack|Exhaust Stack's]] emissions by eight times.
*The [[Exhaust Stack]] uses one '''Filter''' per 120,000 liters of [[Exhaust]].

{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|title1=Hydrogen|research=Electrolysis Plant|sellValue={{Money|0.02}}|itemImage=Icon-hydrogen.png|resValue={{RP|0.5x }}}}
==Information==
'''Hydrogen''' is a versatile fluid that can be made from [[Water]] via an [[Electrolysis Plant]]. It is an essential part in [[Tungsten Carbide Plate|Tungsten Carbide]] and [[Hydrochloric Acid]] production. It is also a [[Pollution]] free element, as [[Gas Burner|burning]] produces none.

==Usage==
'''Hydrogen''' can be used in making [[Hydrochloric Acid]], [[Powdered Tungsten Carbide]], [[Naphtha]], [[Light Oil]], and can be used as a pollution-free alternative to [[Refined Gas]] in the [[Gas Burner]]. However this is not advised due to the net produced power is far lower than a [[Geothermal Well]].

