{{Item|title1=Distilled Water|itemImage=icon-distilled-water.png|research=Oil Fracking|sellValue={{Money|1}}|resValue={{RP|0.3x }}}}
==Information ==
'''Distilled Water''' is a variant of [[Water]] used primarily in the [[Coal Power Plant]]. It can be created by either using:

* [[Water Treatment Plant]]s
** [[Water Treatment Plant]]s need around 64 liters of [[Water]] , {{Power|2MMF}} (assuming {{Heat|400}} steam is inputted) and 90L of [[Steam]] per second. (It is highly recommended that the [[Steam]] [[Temperature]] is around {{Heat|400}} to ensure the [[Water Treatment Plant]] is the maximum efficiency)
**The [[Water Treatment Plant]] can only produce 64 liters of '''Distilled Water''' per second, even with {{Heat|400}} [[Steam]] in the input compared to the huge '''Distilled Water''' requirement of a [[Coal Power Plant|Coal Power Plant]], making it almost a requirement to recycle the '''Distilled Water'''.

* [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]]
** The [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] requires around 25 liters of [[Water]] and{{Power|625kMF/s}} to produce 17 liters of [[Distilled Water]] per second, with 8 liters of [[Concentrated Salt Solution]] per second as an byproduct.

* [[Polisher]]
** The [[Polisher]] is mostly used in [[Coal Power Plant]] setups

The [[Water Treatment Plant]] can only produce 64 liters of '''Distilled Water''' per second, even with {{Heat|400}} [[Steam]] in the input compared to the monstrous '''Distilled Water''' requirement of [[Coal Power Plant|Coal Power Plants]], making it almost a requirement to recycle the '''Distilled Water'''.

It is also not recommended to sell it because it only gives {{Money|1}} per unit.

[[Category:Fluids]]
==Usage==
Some uses of it include the following:  

* '''Distilled Water''' is the second main material in the energy production of [[Coal Power Plant]], (the first being [[Coal|Coal.]])

* '''Distilled Water''' could be used in heating, transferring 20% more heat to [[Boiler|Boilers]].

* '''Distilled Water''' can also be used in [[Scrubber|Scrubbers]], and remove {{Pollution|6.29}}/hr.

* Another use of it is producing 17 [[Sulfuric Acid]] when inputting 20 [[Sulfur Trioxide]], with 20 '''Distilled Water''' and 2 [[Sulfuric Acid]] into a [[Chemical Reactor]].

* It also outputs 5 [[Hydrochloric Acid]], when given 20 [[Chlorine]] with 20 [[Hydrogen]], and 5 '''Distilled Water''' also in a [[Chemical Reactor]].
