{{Item|research=Electrolysis Plant|sellValue={{Money|0.2|size=8}}|itemImage=Icon-chlorine.png|resValue={{RP|0.5x }}}}
==Information==
'''Chlorine''' is a resource that can only be extracted by splitting [[Concentrated Salt Solution]] in an [[Electrolysis Plant]]. Each [[Electrolysis Plant]] can produce up to two liters of '''Chlorine''' per second, rendering it relatively easy to obtain in bulk.

==Usage==
Though '''Chlorine''' sells for only {{Money|0.2}}, its value resides in its wide variety of applications. '''Chlorine''' can be placed inside of a [[Paper Mill]] to make the stated machine twice as efficient, a property that shines in low-[[Pollution]] worlds where [[Tree]] growth is extremely slow, if paper is needed. '''Chlorine''' can also be combined with [[Distilled Water]] and [[Hydrogen]] in a [[Chemical Reactor]], yielding [[Hydrochloric Acid]]. This acid is significantly easier to produce when compared to [[Sulfuric Acid]], allowing it to function as a compact late-game alternative to the latter.

