{{Item|itemImage=Icon-oxygen.png|sellValue={{money|0.1}}|research=Electrolysis Plant|resValue={{RP|0.5x }}}}
==Information==
'''Oxygen''' is a gas that can be obtained by separating [[Water]] in the [[Electrolysis Plant]]. It primarily functions as an optional additive for the [[Oxidation Plant]], accelerating the machine's processing time by four times.

==Usage==
In the vast majority of cases, '''Oxygen''' acts as a useless byproduct of [[Hydrogen]] production lines, and as such it is encouraged to let the [[Electrolysis Plant]] void it. If [[Electrolysis Plant|Electrolysis Plants]] are placed in close proximity to [[Oxidation Plant|Oxidation Plants]], it is highly recommended to redirect the '''Oxygen''' output to the stated machines, as it decreases both the [[Oxidation Plant|Oxidation Plant's]] processing time and [[Power]] usage per liter.

