==Information==
The '''Copper Drill Head''' is one of the [[Drill Heads]] available to be used in the [[Mineshaft Drill]].

It can be made in the [[Lathe]], using 700 [[Copper Ingot]] as the input material. The recipe takes one minute to complete, before outputting the '''Copper Drill Head'''.

The '''Copper Drill Head''' has the lowest durability out of all [[Drill Heads]], which makes it the deficient option when it comes to inputs in the [[Mineshaft Drill]]. However, it is the fastest [[Drill Heads|Drill Head]] to craft both in terms of required material and production time, making it useful for temporary shallow-drilling [[Mineshaft Drill]] setups. Once the 1,200 meter threshold is crossed, the '''Copper Drill Head''' immediately becomes obsolete and impractical.

==Recipes==
