{{Top-drill-heads}}
{{Item
|itemImage=icon-steel-drill-head.png
|research=Mineshaft Drill
|sellValue={{Money|190,000}}
|resValue={{RP|125x }}
}}{{PageHeader|Items}}
==Information==
The '''Steel Drill Head''' is one of the drill heads available for use by a [[Mineshaft Drill]]. It is the most commonly used drill head due to its relatively simple production chain and efficient performance. When used in a single [[Mineshaft Drill]] to supply a [[Coal Power Plant]] with [[Coal]], the '''Steel Drill Head''' achieves an effective efficiency of 85.1% across a 28.1 minute drill cycle, producing an average of 45.9 units of [[Coal]] per second. This output is sufficient to fuel a [[Coal Power Plant]], which requires 44 units per second. By comparison, the [[Tungsten Carbide Drill Head]] reaches 95.8% efficiency across a 1.66 hour cycle but provides only an additional 5.8 units of [[Coal]] per second. The higher yield does not generally offset the additional space and [[Money|Cost]] required for a [[Tungsten Carbide Plate]] setup compared to a [[Steel Ingot]] setup.

The '''Steel Drill Head's''' lower-tier counterparts are less effective. The [[Copper Drill Head]] has extremely poor performance, with efficiencies in the low single digits at the common drilling depths of 6000M and 8000M. The [[Iron Drill Head]] is also outclassed, as upgrading [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]] into [[Steel Ingot|Steel Ingots]] requires only a trivial increase in production complexity while providing a significant efficiency gain.

==Production==
A typical setup for producing '''Steel Drill Heads''' begins with creating [[Treated Raw Iron]] in a [[Chemical Reactor]] using [[Hydrochloric Acid]] and [[Raw Iron]]. The resulting [[Treated Raw Iron]] is then [[Liquid Iron|smelted]] and [[Ingot Molder|molded]] into [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]]. These [[Iron Ingot|Iron Ingots]] are further refined into [[Steel Ingot|Steel Ingots]] using [[Coke Fuel]] from a [[Blast Furnace MK2]], with the conversion carried out in either a regular [[Blast Furnace]] or another [[Blast Furnace MK2]] depending on the required scale of '''Steel Drill Head''' production. A '''Steel Drill Head''' is then, finally, produced from the [[Steel Ingot|Steel Ingots]] in a [[Lathe]] before being used by a [[Mineshaft Drill]].

Efficiency ratings for [[Mineshaft Drill]] setups that utilize the '''Steel Drill Head''' can be found by using the [[Mineshaft Drill/Sheet|Mineshaft Drill Calculator]].

==Recipes==
