{{Item|sellValue={{Money|2|size=8}}|itemImage=Icon-concentrated-salt-solution.png|research=Oil Fracking|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}

== Information ==

'''Concentrated Salt Solution''' is produced by processing [[Water]] in an [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] or by combining [[Water]] and [[Medium Earth Fragment]]s in a [[Pressurized Water Filter]]. It is generated as a byproduct in industrial operations involving the [[Mineshaft Drill]] for large-scale [[Raw Iron]] production or in facilities requiring [[Distilled Water]]. The substance is a primary component in the production of [[Sodium Hydroxide Solution]].

An [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] is capable of producing up to 8 liters of '''Concentrated Salt Solution''' per second, representing the highest output volume achievable by any single production facility.

== Usage ==

The primary application of '''Concentrated Salt Solution''' is in the synthesis of [[Sodium Hydroxide Solution]]. It is also utilized in industrial processes requiring [[Chlorine]], such as [[Paper]] production or the manufacturing of [[Hydrochloric Acid]]. In [[Sodium Hydroxide Solution]] production, it serves as the sole required ingredient.

