{{Item|title1=Table Salt|itemImage=Icon-table-salt.png|tier=3|research=Oil Fracking/Industrial Firebox|sellValue={{money|4}}|caption-itemImage=is this safe to eat?|resValue={{RP|1x }}}} ==Information== '''Table Salt''' is produced in a few ways, them being by feeding [[Concentrated Salt Solution]] into an [[Industrial Firebox]], putting [[Earth Fragments|Medium Earth Fragments]] in a [[Trommel]], and by the [[Mineshaft Drill]] at 4km. It is also mildly important as it is one of the only two ways to produce [[Hydrochloric Acid]], which is also used in the [[Polisher]].
==Usage== '''Table Salt's''' only use is to make [[Hydrochloric Acid]] from [[Sulfuric Acid]]. At first look this doesn't seem that good because normally the player would rather make [[Hydrochloric Acid]] directly with [[Hydrogen]], [[Chlorine]] and [[Distilled Water]] but this recipe is actually really good if the player need <big>LOTS</big> of [[Sulfuric Acid]] and have to take advantage of space or models so the player can do this instead of the traditional way.
