{{Item|itemImage=Icon-galvanized-steel.png|caption-itemImage=|tier=4|sellValue={{Money|123|size= 8}}|title1=Galvanized Steel|research=Electrolysis Plant/Oil Fracking|resValue={{RP|33x }}}}

==Information==
'''Galvanized Steel''' is an item made by coating [[Steel Ingot|Steel Ingots]] with [[Zinc]] in a [[Chemical Reactor]]. As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, it has two uses. It sells for {{Money|123}}, and the {{Badge|Little John}} can be obtained by selling 400 units of '''Galvanized Steel''' in a [[Huge Truck Depot]].

==Usage==
'''Galvanized Steel''' has only two uses, that is being a poor money source, and the ability to gain the {{Badge|Little John}}. Selling '''Galvanized Steel''' is NOT recommended as it requires a high cost, for low income.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=zinc|Input1Amount=5|input2=steel-ingot|Input2Amount=20|Mamyflux=600kMF|output1=galvanized-steel|Output1Amount=20|machine=Chemical Reactor|time=5}}

==Trivia==
*The {{Badge|Little John}} references the meme, [https://www.youtube.com/@HomeDesign365 Home Design] videos.
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|research=Electrolysis plant|sellValue={{money|10}}|itemImage=Icon-sodium-hydroxide-solution.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Sodium Hydroxide Solution''' is a liquid ingredient that can be made in an [[Electrolysis Plant]] using [[Concentrated Salt Solution]]; One [[Electrolysis Plant]] can produce up to six liters of '''Sodium Hydroxide''' every 30 seconds, which translates to roughly one liter every five seconds.

'''Sodium Hydroxide Solution''' can be used in a [[Polisher]] to polish [[Condensate]] back into [[Distilled Water]] for reuse. Since each [[Polisher]] requires one liter of '''Sodium Hydroxide''' per second, five [[Electrolysis Plant|Electrolysis Plants]] are required to supply one of the stated.

==Usage==
The only current use of '''Sodium Hydroxide''' is to be used in a [[Polisher]] for the polishing of [[Condensate]], playing a role in the [[Coal Power Plant]] production. Note the five to one ratio to avoid shortages.

[[Chlorine]] is also produced along with '''Sodium Hydroxide''' as it is electrolyzed; the [[Chlorine]] can be utilized to make [[Hydrochloric Acid]] in the [[Chemical Reactor]] or making [[Paper]] in the Paper Mill. An [[Pipes|Overflow Gate]] should be installed on the [[Chlorine]] output in order to avoid clogs.

If only the [[Hydrochloric Acid]] is desired, the '''Sodium Hydroxide''' can simply be stored or sold. 

