==Trivia==
*'''Zinc''', with the appearance with an ingot, does not include "Ingot" in its name unlike the other Ingots.
*As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, the [[Electrolysis Plant]]'s [[Zinc]] [[Recipe Book|Recipe]] is bugged and does not consume any of the [[Zinc Sulfate]]. As such, it will continuously output [[Zinc]] unless the machine's [[Power]] is cut.
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=icon-graphite-zinc-electrode.png|sellValue={{Money|60}}|research=Precision Assembler|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Graphite-Zinc Electrodes''' can be made with [[Coal]] and [[Zinc]] in a [[Precision Assembler]], and can be used to produce [[Uncharged Lithium-Ion Battery|Uncharged Lithium-Ion Batteries]]. For almost all purposes, these electrodes are generally considered to be inferior to [[Graphite-Iron Electrode|Graphite-Iron Electrodes]], as the latter is significantly easier to produce at no cost to practicality.

==Usage==
Although they are far outclassed by [[Graphite-Iron Electrode|Graphite-Iron Electrodes]] for use in most [[Lithium Battery Pack]] setups, they have an extremely niche use in ore nodes worlds. Due to a bug in the [[Electrolysis Plant]], the stated machine will indefinitely yield [[Zinc]] with no need for a [[Zinc Sulfate]] input, completely eliminating the need for any ore extractors. However, the practicality of this niche usage is greatly hindered by the [[Electrolysis Plant|Electrolysis Plant's]]{{Power|750kMF/s}} toll, requiring approximately 30 times more [[Power]] per ingot ({{Power|38.7kMF/ingot}} versus{{Power|1.125MF/ingot}}).

