{{Item|research=Advanced Assembler|header1=Information|sellValue={{money|120}}|itemImage=icon-dynamite.png|resValue={{RP|25x }}}}
==Information==
'''Dynamite''' is an item that is crafted in the [[Advanced Assembler]] using [[Gunpowder]] and [[Paper]]. Dynamite can be used in the [[Mineshaft Drill]] to dig down faster, at a rate of 24 meters per unit of '''Dynamite''', without using [[Drill Heads|Drill Head]] durability. Note that '''Dynamite''' DOES NOT give extra resources.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=gunpowder|Input1Amount=6|input2=paper|Input2Amount=6|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|machine=Advanced Assembler|output1=dynamite|Output1Amount=1}}

==Trivia==
*The item is mislabelled. Real-life '''dynamite''' is produced by dipping glycercol in a mixture of 25% nitric acid and 75% [[Sulfuric Acid]], then mixing the resulting nitroglycerin with clay. However, the in-game "'''Dynamite'''" is produced with [[Sulfur]] and [[Coal]], making it a black powder explosive.
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|title1=Gunpowder|caption-itemImage=|tier=3|research=Chemical Reactor|header1=information|sellValue={{money|70}}|itemImage=icon-gunpowder.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}

==Information==
'''Gunpowder''' is an item produced in the [[Chemical Reactor]] using [[Water]], [[Sulfur]], and [[Coal]]. As of {{Update|0.11.3}}, gunpowder only serves as an intermediate material for crafting [[Dynamite]].

==Usage==
'''Gunpowder''' is currently only used to produce [[Dynamite]] in the [[Advanced Assembler]]. While it can be sold for {{Money|70}}, players typically convert it into [[Dynamite]] to use in the [[Mineshaft Drill]] to dig down faster, at a rate of 24 metres per unit of [[Dynamite]].

== Recipes==
{{Production|input1=water|input2=sulfur|input3=coal|time=6|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=gunpowder|machine=Chemical Reactor|Input1Amount=10|Input2Amount=8|Input3Amount=4|Output1Amount=4}}
{{Production|input1=gunpowder|Input1Amount=6|input2=paper|Input2Amount=6|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|machine=Advanced Assembler|output1=dynamite|Output1Amount=1}}

==Trivia==
* In real life, the gunpowder in-game is more accurately known as "black powder", composed of sulfur, charcoal, and potassium nitrate.<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gunpowder</ref>
* This means [[Dynamite]] in-game functions as a traditional black powder explosive rather than a nitroglycerin-based explosive.

