{{Item|title1=Electromagnet|caption-itemImage=|tier=4|research=Advanced Assembler|sellValue={{money|950}}|itemImage=icon-electromagnet.png|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
The '''Electromagnet''' is an item made with an [[Advanced Assembler]], and it is used to make [[Electric Motor|Electric Motors]]. Due to [[Electric Motor|Electric Motors]] currently maintaining a low sell value when the amount of materials needed to produce them is taken into account, the '''Electromagnet''' remains rarely produced by players. It is expected that the '''Electromagnet''' will have greater use in future updates.

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=insulated-wire|Input1Amount=40|input2=steel-rod|Input2Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=electromagnet|Output1Amount=2|machine=Advanced Assembler}}
{{Production|input1=electromagnet|Input1Amount=4|Input2Amount=0.2|input2=ferroaluminium-magnet|input3=steel-rod|Input3Amount=2|input4=steel-plate|Input4Amount=4|input5=machine-oil|Input5Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=electric-motor|Output1Amount=2|machine=Advanced Assembler}}
{{Production|input1=electromagnet|Input1Amount=6|input2=steel-rod|Input2Amount=2|input3=steel-plate|Input3Amount=4|input4=machine-oil|Input4Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=electric-motor|Output1Amount=2|machine=Advanced Assembler}}

==Trivia==
* In real life, '''Electromagnets''' are typically constructed with enameled wire, which uses a thin coat of [[Plastic Pellets|Plastic]] to insulate the wire, instead of [[Rubber]] insulation like in-game. This is due to [[Rubber]] being too thick to adequately dissipate heat and [[Plastic Pellets|Plastic]] insulation being more than capable of preventing short circuits.
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|title1=Electric Motor|caption-itemImage=|tier=4|research=Advanced Assembler|sellValue={{money|4,500}}|itemImage=icon-electric-motor.png|resValue={{RP|200x }}}} == Information == '''Electric Motors''' are an item produced in the [[Advanced Assembler]], and as of now, it is used exclusively for selling. It is not recommended to make '''Electric Motors''' due to the long and complex production process compared to the profit margin. [[Ferroaluminium Magnet|Ferroaluminum Magnets]] can be used to increase the profit margin, but using the stated item brings its challenges, mostly in the procurement of [[Bauxite Residue]] and [[Coke Fuel]]. It can also be used in the creation of [[Cat]] as an required ingredient of the [[Cat Assembler]]. '''Electric Motors''' are pretty much useless, but they will most likely have a use in future updates.
==Production==
===Electromagnet Production:=== The most difficult part of any [[Electromagnet]] production chain is the procurement of [[Naphtha]] for the creation of [[Insulated Wire]]. [[Naphtha|Naptha]] can be synthesized from [[Heavy Oil]] and [[Hydrogen]] in the [[Steam Cracking Plant]] or by placing [[Deep Earth Fragment|Deep Earth Fragments]] and [[Water]] into the [[Grinder]]. However, as both of the above methods are extremely difficult and inefficient, it is best to separate [[Fracking Oil]] in the [[Atmospheric Distillation Plant]] and dispose of the byproducts accordingly.
===[[Machine Oil]] Production:=== [[Machine Oil]] can be produced in two different ways, either by running [[Refined Diesel]] through a [[Filtration Plant]] or by separating [[Heavy Oil]] in an [[Industrial Oil Separator]]. The latter is the recommended method, as it does not require several entire [[Diesel]] production lines. To keep up with the 0.4L/s [[Machine Oil]] demand, two [[Industrial Oil Separator|Industrial Oil Separators]] must be running at maximum capacity. One [[Coal Liquefaction Plant]] can easily sustain said [[Industrial Oil Separator|Industrial Oil Separators]].
==Recipes== {{Production|input1=electromagnet|Input1Amount=4|Input2Amount=0.2|input2=ferroaluminium-magnet|input3=steel-rod|Input3Amount=2|input4=steel-plate|Input4Amount=4|input5=machine-oil|Input5Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=electric-motor|Output1Amount=2|machine=Advanced Assembler}} {{Production|input1=electromagnet|Input1Amount=6|input2=steel-rod|Input2Amount=2|input3=steel-plate|Input3Amount=4|input4=machine-oil|Input4Amount=2|time=5|Mamyflux=200kMF|output1=electric-motor|Output1Amount=2|machine=Advanced Assembler}}{{Production|input1=gasoline|Input1Amount=31|input2=electric-motor|Input2Amount=4|input3=sulfur|Input3Amount=15|time=92|Mamyflux=Maxwell|output1=cat|Output1Amount=1|machine=Cat Assembler}}
==Trivia== *The '''Electric Motor''' recipe is the only recipe that uses the [[Advanced Assembler|Advanced Assembler's]] liquid input. *It is also the only current use for [[Electromagnet|Electromagnets]] and [[Ferroaluminium Magnet|Ferroaluminum Magnets]]. *The '''Electric Motor''' is technically not a finalised item like the [[Template:Items Navbox|Items Navbox]] says so, due to the existence of the [[Cat]]. **However, it should be considered that the [[Cat]] is a limited item. {{Items Navbox}}

