{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-wet-concrete.png|research=Concrete Production|sellValue={{Money|120}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Wet Concrete''' is a stepping stone to either [[Concrete Block|Concrete Blocks]], or the stronger [[Reinforced Concrete Block]]. 

== Usage ==
'''Wet Concrete''' can be produced into [[Concrete Block|Concrete Blocks]] by combining it with [[Water]] into a [[Concrete Plant]], additionally '''Wet Concrete''' can be turned into [[Reinforced Concrete Block|Reinforced Concrete Blocks]] by combining it with [[Steel Rod|Steel Rods]] instead of [[Water]] inside the [[Concrete Plant]].

== Recipes ==
{{Production|input1=cement|Input1Amount=10|input2=aggregate|Input2Amount=20|time=10|Mamyflux=4kMF|output1=wet-concrete|Output1Amount=20|input3=water|Input3Amount=60|machine=Concrete Plant}}
{{Production|input1=wet-concrete|time=10|Mamyflux=4kMF|output1=concrete-block|machine=Concrete Plant|Input1Amount=20|Output1Amount=20|input2=water|Input2Amount=10}}
{{Production|input1=wet-concrete|time=10|Mamyflux=4kMF|output1=reinforced-concrete-block|machine=Concrete Plant|Input1Amount=10|Output1Amount=10|input2=steel-rod|Input2Amount=40}}


[[Category:Items]]
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-concrete-block.png|sellValue={{Money|150}}|research=Concrete Production|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}

== Information ==
'''Concrete Blocks''' are produced by mixing [[Cement]] and [[Water]] in a [[Concrete Plant]]. These blocks can be used to prevent the spread of radiation within a world.

== Usage ==
A total of 50,000 '''Concrete Blocks''' can be utilized to repair a [[Nuclear Power Plant]] following an explosion. Additionally, '''Concrete Blocks''' may be added to an [[Underground Waste Facility]] to enable the storage of any items and liquids.

== Recipes ==
{{Production|input1=wet-concrete|time=10|Mamyflux=4kMF|output1=concrete-block|machine=Concrete Plant|Input1Amount=20|Output1Amount=20|input2=water|Input2Amount=10}}

[[Category:Items]]
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-reinforced-concrete-block.png|research=Brick Production|sellValue={{Money|630}}|resValue={{RP|4x }}}}
==Information==
'''Reinforced Concrete''' is an Item Produced by the [[Concrete Plant]]. It has no other use than to be sold.

== Usage ==
Unlike its "Inferior" Counterpart, it cannot be used to fill a destroyed [[Nuclear Power Plant]], nor can it be used in an [[Underground Waste Facility]], to get rid of Waste.

== Recipes ==
{{Production|input1=wet-concrete|time=10|Mamyflux=4kMF|output1=reinforced-concrete-block|machine=Concrete Plant|Input1Amount=10|Output1Amount=10|input2=steel-rod|Input2Amount=40}}


[[Category:Items]]
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Stub}}
{{Item|itemImage=Icon-cement.png|research=Concrete Production|sellValue={{Money|30}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
'''Cement''' is a product of [[Rawmix]] in an [[Industrial Kiln]] and an ingredient to [[Wet Concrete]]. It is an Early to Mid-Game item, being used in concrete production, where they shine in creating [[Reinforced Concrete Block|Reinforced Concrete Blocks]].

== Usage ==
'''Cement''' can be used to create [[Wet Concrete]] in the [[Concrete Plant]] with [[Water]] and [[Aggregate]], which can later be turned into [[Concrete Block|Concrete Blocks]] or [[Reinforced Concrete Block|Reinforced Concrete Blocks]] using more [[Water]] and [[Steel Rod|Steel Rods]] respectively.

