{{Stub}}
{{Item|title1=Raw Uranium|itemImage=Icon-raw-uranium.png|research=Mineshaft Drill|sellValue={{Money|54}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
For other uses, see [[Raw Uranium (disambiguation)]].
{{Quote|Obtained from mineshaft drill at deep levels}}
==Information==
'''Raw Uranium''' is an item used to make [[Mixed Uranium Oxides]] and obtained when drilling in deep levels using the [[Mineshaft Drill]]. It is not recommended to sell this item due to it's low sell price of {{Money|54}}, and instead should be processed into [[Mixed Uranium Oxides]], where it can make [[Low Enrichment Fuel Rod]]s and [[MOX Fuel Rod]]s. Its enrichment process is slow, hence it's not recommended to farm this item.
==Usage==
'''Raw Uranium''' is to be used in an [[Ore Enrichment Facility]] to be processed into [[Mixed Uranium Oxides]], where [[Low Enrichment Fuel Rod]] and [[MOX Fuel Rod]]s can be made.
==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=raw-uranium|input2=hydrochloric-acid|input3=sodium-hydroxide-solution|time=10|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=mixed-uranium-oxides|output2=sand|output3=residue|machine=Ore Enrichment Facility|Input1Amount=20|Input2Amount=1|Input3Amount=1|Output1Amount=5|Output2Amount=20|Output3Amount=60}} 
{{Production|input1=raw-uranium|input2=sulfuric-acid|input3=sodium-hydroxide-solution|time=10|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=mixed-uranium-oxides|output2=sand|output3=residue|machine=Ore Enrichment Facility|Input1Amount=20|Input2Amount=1|Input3Amount=1|Output1Amount=6|Output2Amount=10|Output3Amount=60}} 
==Trivia==
* '''Raw Uranium''' was added in the {{Update|1.0}} update.
* Although '''Raw Uranium''' and [[Uranium]] sound similar, they are completely different items and cannot be used interchangeably in [[Machine]]s.
* A certain player likes anything associated with this item.
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Stub}}
{{Item|title1=Contaminated Water|itemImage=Icon-contaminated-water.png|research=Nuclear Power Plant|sellValue={{Money|-241}}|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}
==Information==
'''Contaminated Water''' is one of the main outputs from a [[Nuclear Power Plant]], mainly coming from cooling the [[Standard Fuel Rod|Fuel Rods]] inside a [[Nuclear Power Plant]].

==Usage==

Heated '''Contaminated Water,''' from the pump outputs of a [[Nuclear Power Plant]], should be used to heat a [[Heat Exchanger]] in order to produce [[High Pressure Steam]], with it later being returned back to the [[Nuclear Power Plant]]. However, if the '''Contaminated Water''' is from draining a flooded reactor hall or through the use of the Letdown Valve it should be recycled back into [[Distilled Water]] by using a [[Water Treatment Plant]]. 

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=contaminated-water|Input1Amount=64|input2=steam|Input2Amount=363.6ÂºC 90|time=1|Mamyflux=2MMF|machine=Water Treatment Plant|output1=distilled-water|Output1Amount=64}}
{{Production|input1=contaminated-water|Input1Amount=400|input2=distilled-water|Input2Amount=400|time=1|Mamyflux=0MF|machine=Heat Exchanger|output1=contaminated-water|Output1Amount=400|output2=high-pressure-steam|Output2Amount=12000}}
{{Production|input1=contaminated-water|Input1Amount=400|input2=distilled-water|Input2Amount=400|time=1|Mamyflux=0MF|machine=Vertical Heat Exchanger|output1=contaminated-water|Output1Amount=400|output2=high-pressure-steam|Output2Amount=12000}}

== Trivia ==

* '''Contaminated Water''' is the only fluid to sell for less than [[Residue]], beating it by ~41.55 times. However, this is beaten by Radiactive Waste for the lowest sell price in the game. 

