{{Item|itemImage=Icon-zirconium-chloride.png|research=Chemical Reactor|sellValue={{Money|30}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}

== Information ==
'''Zirconium Chloride''' is produced combining by [[Raw Zirconium]] and [[Chlorine]] in a [[Chemical Reactor]]. Then to be combine it with [[Distilled Water]] to obtain [[Zirconium Dioxide]].

== Usage ==
'''Zirconium Chloride''' is used in the production of [[Zirconium Dioxide]], and later [[Zirconium Rod|Zirconium Rods]]. [[Hydrochloric Acid]] is a waste product of this process, however it can be used in other processes that use small amounts of acid, like making [[Mixed Uranium Oxides]] which uses 0.1L/s per [[Ore Enrichment Facility]].

== Recipes ==
