{{Item|title1=Reprocessed Uranium|itemImage=Icon-reprocessed-uranium.png|research=Advanced Chemical Plant|sellValue={{Money|0}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}
==Information==
[[Reprocessed Uranium]] is a nuclear material obtained from [[Mixed Fissile Oxides]] in the [[Chemical Plant]]. It is used to produce [[Slightly Enriched UF6 Gas]], which is a precursor for [[Enriched UO2 Pellets]].
==Usage==
[[Reprocessed Uranium]] is processed in the [[Chemical Plant]] to produce [[Slightly Enriched UF6 Gas]] when combined with [[Hydrofluoric Acid]]. It is obtained alongside [[Plutonium Oxide Pellets]] during the separation of [[Mixed Fissile Oxides]].

There is an alternative route to produce Slightly Enriched UF6 Gas that does not require Reprocessed Uranium, starting from [[Yellowcake]] and [[Hydrofluoric Acid]].
==Recipes==
