{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-boric-acid.png|research=Advanced Chemical Plant|sellValue={{Money|1,500}}|resValue={{RP|12x }}}}

== Information ==
[[Boric Acid]] is a refined chemical intermediate used in nuclear production chains. It is produced by processing [[Impure Boron]] with acidic reagents inside the [[Chemical Plant]]. It also generates small amounts of [[Residue]] as a byproduct.

Boric Acid serves as an important precursor for creating [[Boron]], which is required to assemble [[Control Rod]]s in the [[Precision Assembler]].
== Usage ==
[[Boric Acid]] is primarily consumed to produce [[Boron]] in the [[Industrial Firebox]]. Boron is then combined with a [[Zirconium Rod]] to manufacture [[Control Rod]]s, a critical component for nuclear fuel management.

== Recipes ==
