=== Information ===
{{Quote|This item is HIGHLY radioactive. Do NOT dump and do NOT store it in silos or tanks. Must be disposed of in Underground Waste Facility}}
The '''Spent MOX Fuel''' is a byproduct released during the {{Update|1.0}} update, which is made by the [[Nuclear Power Plant]] when a [[MOX Fuel Rod|Mox Fuel Rod]] has been used. This [[Item]] is highly [[Radiation|Radioactive]] and should be stored in the [[Underground Waste Facility]].

===Usage===
'''Spent MOX Fuel''' has no use, apart from being stored into the [[Underground Waste Facility]], and cannot be reprocessed into more [[Fuel Rod]]s.

===Trivia===
* The '''Spent MOX Fuel''' icon is a purple waste barrel, similar to those used to store [[Radiation|Radioactive]] [[Item]]s in real life.
* '''Spent MOX Fuel''' is one of the waste products made by the [[Nuclear Power Plant]].
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Stub}}{{Item|itemImage=Icon-argon.png|sellValue={{Money|2}}|research=Air Separation Unit|resValue={{RP|0x }}}}

== Information ==
The '''Argon''' is a chemical element that is produced from vaporizing [[Liquid Argon]]. It is one of the three elements, alongside with [[Oxygen]] and [[Nitrogen]] that can be produced with an [[Air Separation Unit]] to capture its liquid state, which is then inputted to the [[Vaporizer]]. 

== Usage ==
'''Argon''' currently has a few share of uses, primarily being used as an ingredient to produce [[Reprocessed Uranium]] and [[Plutonium Oxide Pellets]] via the [[Chemical Plant]]. 

Oher uses here include being an alternative to produce acids such as [[Sulfuric Acid]] and [[Hydrochloric Acid]], consuming less power when producing the latter. However, these crafting recipes are limited to only the [[Chemical Plant]] and only uses [[Distilled Water]] as the one of the primary solvents.

== Recipes ==
{{Production|time=1|Mamyflux=15kMF|input1=liquid-argon|Input1Amount=3|output1=argon|Output1Amount=90|machine=Vaporizer}}
{{Production|input1=mixed-fissile-oxides|Input1Amount=0.5|input2=hydrochloric-acid|Input2Amount=0.5|input3=sodium-hydroxide-solution|Input3Amount=0.5|input4=argon|Input4Amount=10|time=1|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=residue|Output1Amount=3|output2=reprocessed-uranium|Output2Amount=0.1|output3=plutonium-oxide-pellets|Output3Amount=0.05|machine=Chemical Plant}}
{{Production|input1=sulfur-trioxide|Input1Amount=14|input2=distilled-water|Input2Amount=11|input3=argon|Input3Amount=70|time=1|Mamyflux=1.5MMF|output1=sulfuric-acid|Output1Amount=11|output2=residue|Output2Amount=2|machine=Chemical Plant}}
{{Production|input1=chlorine|Input1Amount=20|input2=hydrogen|Input2Amount=20|input3=distilled-water|Input3Amount=10|input4=argon|Input4Amount=20|time=1|Mamyflux=1.5MMF|output1=hydrochloric-acid|Output1Amount=10|machine=Chemical Plant}}

== Trivia ==

* Based on how the element is produced and manufactured, the in-game '''Argon''' produces around four times the actual amount when compared to real life basis. This implies that the air in-game contains around 3.85% of '''Argon''', in contrast to the usual 0.93%.
* '''Argon''' is considered the most stable element amongst the other 2 elements, [[Nitrogen]] and [[Oxygen]].
** '''Argon''' falls under the "Noble Gas" category in the periodic table, where 8 valence electrons are present in its outer shell as an element alone, making it inert and stable.
