{{Stub}}
{{Item|itemImage=Icon-fission-byproducts.png|sellValue={{Money|-5000000}}|resValue={{RP|0x }}|research=Advanced Oxidation Plant, Ore Enrichment Facility|title1=Fission Byproducts}}
== Information ==
{{Quote|This item is HIGHLY radioactive. Do NOT dump and do NOT store it in silos or tanks. Must be disposed of in Underground Waste Facility.}}'''Fission Byproducts''' is a radioactive byproduct that is produced from {{Tier||4}} machines such as the [[Ore Enrichment Facility]] and [[Advanced Oxidation Plant]] to process [[Mixed Fissile Nitrates]] and [[Mixed Fissile Oxides]], respectively. Akin to the purpose of [[Spent MOX Fuel]] and other radioactive-related resources, this waste product cannot be used for any methods of further production. 

Storing this byproduct, along with other radioactive materials, is ill-advised as this may cause significant amounts of [[Radiation]] if stored in silos, sold by liquid trucks, or discarded using the [[Incinerator]] and/or [[Item Dump]]. The most conventional way to dispose the said byproduct is to use the [[Underground Waste Facility]], as this will dissipate it completely without negatively affecting the player's world.

==Usage==
Since '''Fission Byproducts''' serves no purpose and sells for a huge negative amount of [[Money]], disposing of it can be really difficult if the player has no access to the [[Underground Waste Facility]], as it cannot be treated as to how [[Residue]] is conventionally stored via silos.

== Recipes ==
{{Production|input1=mixed-fissile-nitrates|Input1Amount=1|input2=limestone|Input2Amount=10|input3=oxygen|Input3Amount=120|input4=steam|Input4Amount=90|time=2|Mamyflux=1MMF|output1=mixed-fissile-oxides|Output1Amount=1|output2=fission-byproducts|Output2Amount=4|output3=residue|Output3Amount=20|machine=Advanced Oxidation Plant}}
{{Production|input1=mixed-fissile-nitrates|Input1Amount=1|input2=limestone|Input2Amount=2|input3=tributyl-phosphate|Input3Amount=6|input4=steam|Input4Amount=90|time=2|Mamyflux=1MMF|output1=mixed-fissile-oxides|Output1Amount=2|output2=fission-byproducts|Output2Amount=2|output3=residue|Output3Amount=15|machine=Advanced Oxidation Plant}}
{{Production|input1=spent-fuel|Input1Amount=50|input2=hydrochloric-acid|Input2Amount=1|input3=nitrogen|Input3Amount=120|time=10|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=mixed-fissile-nitrates|Output1Amount=5|output2=fission-byproducts|Output2Amount=95|output3=residue|Output3Amount=5|machine=Ore Enrichment Facility}}
{{Production|input1=spent-fuel|Input1Amount=50|input2=sulfuric-acid|Input2Amount=1|input3=nitrogen|Input3Amount=120|time=10|Mamyflux=500kMF|output1=mixed-fissile-nitrates|Output1Amount=7|output2=fission-byproducts|Output2Amount=93|output3=residue|Output3Amount=10|machine=Ore Enrichment Facility}}

== Trivia ==

*As of {{Update|1.0}}, '''Fission Byproducts''' is rendered as the quickest way to lose money, selling for {{Money|-5,000,000}}.
*'''Fission Byproducts''' can not only cause pollution, but also radiation to a player's world, along with [[Spent MOX Fuel]] and [[Spent Fuel]].
*With the extreme price of {{Money|-5,000,000}}''', Fission Byproduct(s)''' have the lowest sell price in the game, having a sell price 862068.97x less than [[Residue]], the item with the lowest sell price before {{Update|1.0}}. It is also 5x less than [[Spent Fuel]].
**Assuming all the fission byproduct created in an [[Ore Enrichment Facility]] was sold, it would make {{Money|-46,500,000}} a second if it used [[Sulfuric Acid]] and {{Money|-47,500,000}} if using [[Hydrochloric Acid]].

