{{stub}}
{{Item|itemImage=Icon-ammonia.png|research=Advanced Chemical Plant|sellValue={{Money|1}}|resValue={{RP|15x }}}}
==Information==
'''Ammonia''' is a chemical produced by bonding 30 [[Hydrogen]] atoms and 10 [[Nitrogen]] atoms via the Chemical Plant. It can be used for items such as [[Yellowcake]], [[Powdered Tungsten Carbide]], and [[Hardened Plastic Pellets]].
==Usage==
'''Ammonia''' currently has 3 different uses to produce different kinds of product, these can be used to;

*Produce [[Yellowcake]] as an alternative substance to [[Oxygen]] for a higher quantity of the latter, along with [[Mixed Uranium Oxides]] and [[Sulfuric Acid]] using the [[Advanced Oxidation Plant]].
*Produce [[Powdered Tungsten Carbide]] along with other more materials and can be used as an alternative for the [[Chemical Reactor]].
<li>Allow the primary production of [[Hardened Plastic Pellets]]. Generally mixed with [[Naphtha]] and are inputted inside the [[Chemical Plant]].</li>

==Recipes==
{{Production|input1=hydrogen|Input1Amount=30|input2=nitrogen|Input2Amount=10|time=1|Mamyflux=100kMF|output1=ammonia|Output1Amount=20|machine=Chemical Plant}}
{{Production|input1=mixed-uranium-oxides|Input1Amount=10|input2=ammonia|Input2Amount=100|input3=sulfuric-acid|Input3Amount=100|time=40|Mamyflux=1MMF|output1=yellowcake|Output1Amount=8|machine=Advanced Oxidation Plant}}
{{Production|input1=deep-earth-fragment|Input1Amount=6|input2=coal|Input2Amount=40|input3=sulfuric-acid|Input3Amount=6|input4=ammonia|Input4Amount=60|time=4|Mamyflux=1MMF|output1=powdered-tungsten-carbide|Output1Amount=7|output2=residue|Output2Amount=20|machine=Ore Enrichment Facility}}
{{Production|input1=ammonia|Input1Amount=25|input2=naphtha|Input2Amount=5|time=5|Mamyflux=1MMF|output1=hardened-plastic-pellets|machine=Chemical Plant|Output1Amount=50}}

== Trivia ==

* Despite the game's recipe of 25 liters of '''Ammonia''' and 5 liters of [[Naphtha]] are able to produce [[Hardened Plastic Pellets]], the two products alone cannot directly produce to a more refined version of plastic for real-life scenarios.
** In reality, these products can used to indirectly produce these kinds of plastics, but are not the main sources to produce the latter.
* '''Ammonia''' can sometimes be called as "Nitrogen trihydride (''NH<sub>3</sub>'')" due to the fact that this chemical compound contains 3 hydrogen atoms and 1 nitrogen atom as the central atom.
{{Items Navbox}}

{{Item|itemImage=Icon-boron.png|sellValue={{Money|0}}|resValue={{RP|1x }}|research=Advanced Chemical Plant}}

== Information ==
'''Boron''' is a material that is produced from inputting [[Boric Acid]] via the [[Industrial Firebox]]. This vital item, along with the [[Zirconium Rod]], is primarily used to produce [[Control Rod|Control Rods]] via the [[Precision Assembler]], where it is then inputted to the [[Nuclear Power Plant]].

When selling, it is '''HIGHLY''' not recommended for '''Boron''' to be sold solely, as they provide no sell value at all. It is best to sell its liquid state counterpart, the [[Boric Acid]], selling for {{Money|1500}}. Additionally, it can also be processed with the [[Zirconium Rod]] to produce [[Control Rod|Control Rods]], which sells at a significant value of {{Money|150000}}.

== Usage ==
As of {{Update|1.0}}, the only primary use of '''Boron''' is to produce [[Control Rod|Control Rods]] using the [[Precision Assembler]] to produce the latter, requiring 40 units of '''Boron''' and 1 [[Zirconium Rod]].

== Recipes ==
{{Production|input1=boric-acid|output1=boron|Input1Amount=2|Output1Amount=1|time=1|machine=Industrial Firebox|Mamyflux=0MF}}
{{Production|input1=zirconium-rod|input2=boron|Input1Amount=1|Input2Amount=40|output1=control-rod|Output1Amount=1|time=5|machine=Precision Assembler|Mamyflux=1MMF}}

== Trivia ==

* As of {{Update|1.0}}, '''Boron''' only has one source of obtaining it and one use of the latter. However, it is still a vital item to produce as it acts like a bridge between two vital products such as the [[Boric Acid]] and [[Control Rod]].

