{{Stub}}{{Item|itemImage=Icon-enriched-uo2-pellets.png|sellValue={{Money|256}}|research=Advanced Chemical Plant|resValue={{RP|1x }}}}

== Information ==
Enriched UO2 Pellets is a key item in [[Standard Fuel Rod]] manufacturing, it is created by inputting [[Enriched UF6 Gas]] with either [[Tributyl Phosphate]] or [[Hydrogen]] in the [[Chemical Plant]], which is then used to create a Standard Fuel Rod in the [[Precision Assembler]]

== Usage ==
Enriched UO2 Pellets are used with a [[Zirconium Rod]] to create a [[Standard Fuel Rod]], which has more lifetime than its [[Low Enrichment Fuel Rod|Low Enrichment counterpart]] but has less lifetime than its [[MOX Fuel Rod|MOX Fuel counterpart]], other than that it can not be used elsewhere, and selling it is not recommended as it only sells for {{Money|256}}, and also because it outputs either 0.05 units with Tributyl Phosphate(20 seconds for 1 unit) or 0.01 units with Hydrogen(100 seconds or 1 minute and 40 seconds for 1 unit).

